title: hamburger noodle stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until hot.
Stir.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: In a very large bowl or a 6-quart pot, beat egg yolks with a large whisk or a portable electric mixer at high speed until pale and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating constantly, until thick and pale.
Add 1/8 teaspoon nutmeg.
Pour in whiskey, beating constantly.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Add bay leaf and onion to water to boil chicken.
Remove chicken when cooked.

title: refrigerated sweet pickles
directions: Mix ingredients in a pan, stir till mixed well.
Slice enough cucumbers to fill a large jar.
In large jar put thinly sliced pickles and 1 small sliced onion.
Pour cold solution over pickles and put in refrigerator.
Will be ready to eat in 2 or 3 days. Will keep for a long time..............very good.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Boil potatoes in salted water until tender.
Cool potatoes, then peel.
Grate with coarse grater.
Add sour cream, cheese, onion, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly. Turn into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Smooth top with spatula.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease pan.
Slice apples; sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Mix butter, brown sugar and flour until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Spread over apples.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: english sherry trifle
directions: Make Jell-O according to directions; let cool.
Make custard. Let cool. Split ladyfingers and spread with raspberry jam. Arrange in fancy dish.
Carefully spoon sherry evenly over ladyfingers; let stand 1/2 hour.
Pour cooled Jell-O over lady fingers; let it set.
Pour cooled custard over Jell-O.
Add 1/2 teaspoon sugar and a few drops of vanilla to whipping cream and whip until stiff.
Pipe or spread whipping cream on top of trifle and decorate with slivered almonds and cherries.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar, peanut butter and brown sugar. Add the egg and vanilla. Beat well and blend in the flour, soda and salt. Shape into balls of 1 teaspoon each.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven and top with Hershey's Kiss, pressing down firmly. Bake 2 to 5 minutes more.

title: cream soup base
directions: Mix and store in an airtight container.
To reconstitute, mix 1/3 cup dry mix with 1 1/4 cups of water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Makes enough to fill about 9 soup cans.

title: spicy pork roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim roast of excess fat; wash and pat dry.
Sprinkle roast with salt, pepper and garlic salt, then rub in.
Do this on all sides.
Place roast in Pyrex or earthenware baking dish.
Add rice wine and water to the dish.
Sprinkle 5 spice powder on meat, but do add some to the liquids.
Cover dish tightly with aluminum foil, then place in middle of oven to bake. Bake for 35 minutes per pound; one half hour before done, remove foil.
Roast is done when internal temperature reaches 180°.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel, slice and separate onions.
Cook in butter until golden brown.
Add hot water and simmer until tender.
Add stock, reserving 4 tablespoons to blend with flour when cool.
Add and stir into mixture.
Season with salt and freshly ground pepper. Cook only a few minutes.
Pour into soup bowls.
Place squares of toast in center.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Run under broiler to slightly brown cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger. Cook spaghetti until tender; drain. Put spaghetti sauce on top of layered browned hamburger and cooked spaghetti. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Take from oven and put Mozzarella cheese on top and place back in oven until cheese melts.

title: chicken cheese lasagne
directions: Mix melted margarine and flour in saucepan and cook 1 minute. Add garlic, salt, milk and chicken broth.
Stir until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add cheeses, onion, basil, oregano and pepper.
Layer lasagne, creamed cheese, milk and chicken broth mixture, chicken and spinach, repeating until used.
Put grated Parmesan on top.

title: haystacks
directions: Heat beans.
Pour over cooked brown rice or corn chips and layer the rest of the ingredients on top.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Mix ingredients and place on lettuce leaf.
Yield:
1 serving. Carbohydrate 6 g, protein 1 g, fat 2 g, calories 46.
One serving = 1 vegetable exchange, 1/2 fat exchange.

title: oatmeal coconut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Drop by spoonfuls on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: minestrone soup(hamburg soup)
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Boil water; add all ingredients until orzo and carrots are cooked.
Add salt, pepper or garlic salt to taste.

title: punch
directions: Boil water and sugar 3 minutes; cool.
Mix other ingredients with water except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Add onion to broccoli and steam.
Drain.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until well blended.
Add milk gradually and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli and remaining ingredients. Cook until cheese is melted.
Serves 5.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Add cut up dates, nuts and orange slices which have been dredged in part of flour.
Mix well.
Bake in well-greased stem or Bundt pan.
Bake over pan of water.
Bake slow at 250° until done.

title: creamy leek potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine leeks, potatoes, chicken broth and salt.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Pour mixture in blender or food processor.
Blend slightly.
Return to saucepan.
Stir in sour cream, milk and chives.
Heat gently.
Makes 8 1/2 cups. Preparation time:
20 minutes.
Cooking time:
15 minutes.

title: roasted quail
directions: Soak overnight in salted water, 1 part vinegar to 1 part water.
Stew or fry in same manner as chicken.

title: lo-cal date-nut bars
directions: Combine egg and brown sugar in a large bowl; beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) in a medium bowl at high speed until stiff peaks form.
Fold egg whites into beaten egg mixture.
Combine flour and next 5 ingredients; add to egg mixture, stirring until well blended.
Stir in vanilla.

title: granny's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add corn syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Add pecans and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer.

title: vanilla cream pie(or coconut, banana, butterscotch or chocolate)
directions: In a saucepan add sugar, all-purpose flour and/or the cornstarch and salt.
Add milk slowly, mixing well over medium heat until it thickens and boils.
Then cook for 2 minutes more, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir a small amount of mixture into a bowl with the three slightly beaten egg yolks and immediately return to hot mixture.
Cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.

title: mom's lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for two minutes.
Pour into a 9 x 13 greased cake pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Frost with Fluffy Frosting.

title: carnival
directions: Cut sausage into small chunks.
Cut peppers and onions into small pieces.
Steam in electric skillet until peppers and onions are tender.
Remove with a slotted spoon onto serving dish.
This makes a good, quick and easy dish for potluck dinners.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg; add milk, then add vanilla.
Sift in flour and dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and raisins.
Mix well. Spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes or until done.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Simmer all ingredients (except eggs) in saucepan for 10 minutes.
Put eggs in jar and cover with hot mixture.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix meat and seasonings together.
Line bottom of pan with bacon strips.
Put mixture in pan and bake at 350°.
This freezes well.

title: un-sloppy joes
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and celery in 1 1/2 quart microproof casserole.
Cover with casserole lid and cook on HI for 5-7 minutes, stirring once to break up beef; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, mustard and chili powder.
Spoon over bottom halves of buns.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover with top halves of buns. Makes 4 sandwiches.
Total cooking time:
5-7 minutes.

title: hot cheese soup
directions: Cook all vegetables until tender. Add chicken bouillon cubes and soup. Turn to simmer. Add the cheese (cubed) until melted.

title: browned sugar frosting
directions: Put 1 cup sugar into heavy skillet.
Heat over low to medium heat, stirring constantly, until golden brown.
Have 1 cup sugar, milk and butter boiling when sugar is brown.
Add browned sugar to boiling mixture.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat. Beat until cooled and spreading consistency.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pack firmly in greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until brown.
Slice. Serve hot or cold.
Serves 8.

title: banana punch
directions: Heat water and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Mix with all other ingredients except ginger ale.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw until mushy and add ginger ale (may take 2 to 3 hours).
Serve.
Makes about 40 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake uncovered at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Do not beat.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: forever amber candy
directions: Put into a greased 10 x 15 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes or until set.
Have a separate bowl of powdered sugar. Spoon candy mixture into powdered sugar.
Make into balls.
Place on waxed paper; place in freezer.
After frozen, store in airtight container.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: blueberry pie
directions: In large bowl combine blueberries, sugar, flour, lemon rind, cinnamon and salt.
Turn mixture into pastry shell.
Sprinkle berries with lemon juice and dot with butter cut in small pieces. Invert pie shell on top of pie; seal edges and flute.
Cut a few vents for steam.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until crust is golden brown and filling is bubbly.
Serve warm or cool.
A little vanilla ice cream on top makes a very delicious addition.
Makes 2 pies.

title: apple walnut supreme cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine apples and sugar in large bowl and set aside.
In another bowl mix eggs, oil and vanilla; beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with apple mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
To milk, add vinegar and stir.
Set aside to sour and thicken.
Onto waxed paper, sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt.
In a large bowl, beat butter until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar.
Add beaten eggs, 1/2 at a time.
Mix molasses and boiling water.
Stir in gradually.
*Add 1/4 flour mixture and mix well.
Add 1/3 sour milk and blend.
*Repeat, ending with flour mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: poppy seed almond bread
directions: Beat eggs, milk, oil and sugar until mixed well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; add to egg mixture along with the poppy seed and flavorings.
Stir well, but don't overmix.
Bake in small floured and greased loaf pans or muffins.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Makes 4 to 5 mini loaves or 24 muffins.
Bake loaves at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, muffins for 23 to 28 minutes.
Cool and remove from pans.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and chop into bite-size pieces.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into sprayed or greased ovenproof dish (shallow).
Bake 30 minutes at 350° and then broil until brown on top.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Add cooked macaroni, corn, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 7 to 8.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients together in glass baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour until golden brown.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Stir in pumpkin and spices with whisk until well mixed. Spread over cream cheese layer.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix peanut butter and butter together.
Add confectioners sugar.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Chill.
Melt chocolate chips and wax in double boiler.
Dip the balls in the chocolate.

title: (harvey) baked beans
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Heat milk. Add sugar, salt, yeast and shortening; blend well. Add to flour in a large bowl. Add eggs. Work together; let rise until double in bulk. Work down; let rise again. Roll and cut; let rise and then fry in hot oil. Be careful not to puncture doughnut when turning.

title: fireside macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Mix mayonnaise, green pepper, pimento, onion, salt, soup, cream, cheese and macaroni.
Place in casserole.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Combine berries, 1/3 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cornstarch in small pan.
Cook over medium heat 2 or 3 minutes or until thickened (stir continuously); set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add 1 cup of sugar.
Beat on medium speed; add eggs (one at a time).
Beat after each egg.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Alternate with sour cream, add flour mixture with the cream butter (start and end with flour).
Stir in almond extract.
Spoon 1/2 of batter into a 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan.
Spoon on 1/2 of the blueberry sauce, swirl batter; repeat.
Top with pecans.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Dribble with glaze.

title: baked beans
directions: Add all ingredients to beans.
Stir.
Simmer on top of stove on low heat
until thickened to desired consistency.
(They stick more while cooking.)

title: maple pecan roll
directions: Cook all except nuts to soft-ball stage with light stirring. Take from fire; beat until cool.
Turn out on pastry board, dusted with powdered sugar.
Knead until firm, then shape in roll and cover outside with pecan meats.
Put in cold place; slice when firm, using very sharp knife.
Finely chopped pecan meats can be worked through candy while it is being kneaded.

title: tortilla bites
directions: In small bowl combine all ingredients until smooth.
Spread each tortilla with 1/4 cup cheese mixture, spreading evenly to edge.
Tightly roll up in jelly roll fashion.
Place seam side down in shallow dish.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Cut each tortilla into 1-inch slices.
Garnish with shredded carrots or green onions.
Delicious.

title: pea salad
directions: Drain peas. Add to other ingredients. Mix thoroughly.

title: custard pie
directions: Combine ingredients, except nutmeg; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° until set. Baking time should be about 35 minutes total.
The center may still look a bit soft but will set later.
This is also good without the pie shell in small custard cups.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add eggs, 2 at a time.
Add flour, 1/3 at a time.
Mix fruit and nuts last.
Cook in tube cake pan 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 250°.

title: garlic sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in a small bowl.
Microwave on medium for 20 seconds and stir well.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put everything in a 2 quart casserole dish, cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: auntee dee's artichoke dip
directions: Drain hearts and chop.
Mix all three thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: hot sweet pickles
directions: Drain liquid from pickles and cut into 1/4 to 1/2-inch chunks. Place in large crockery bowl and add sugar and Tabasco sauce. Stir several times daily for 2 to 3 days.
It will make its own liquid.
Save all liquid to use when placing pickles in small jars.
Refrigerate.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in water with skins on until done.
Remove potatoes and peel.
Put into a large baking dish, either whole or cut in half.
Slice margarine and put on top of potatoes. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned bread stuffing
directions: Fry hamburger.
Cook onion and celery in butter in a skillet until tender.
Add mixture to bread cubes which have been placed in a large dish.
Sprinkle with seasoning which has been mixed together.
Combine.
Add water and egg.
Toss together with fork. Put in dish or bird and bake.

title: instant nut roll
directions: Combine crumbs, dates or raisins.
Add milk mixed with lemon juice.
Knead well.
Shape into a 3-inch roll.
Wrap in wax paper; store in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: yankee noodle dandies("no-bake summer cookies")
directions: Melt chips in top of double boiler, over boiling water.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in noodles and nuts.
Stir to completely coat. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Chill to firm.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: braised venison
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together. Dip venison in flour mixture to coat well. Brown in fat. Top with onion rings. Sprinkle with garlic salt. Add water and simmer over medium heat for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: fried rice
directions: While rice is cooking, fry the bacon and remove from skillet. Saute the grated carrots and chopped onion.
Crumble the bacon. Add bacon and sauteed vegetables to cooked rice.
Mix ingredients together and salt to taste.

title: fantastic macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions and drain.
Set aside. Combine egg, cottage cheese, sour cream, seasonings and shredded cheese, reserving 1/2 cup to sprinkle on top.
Mix in macaroni. Put in 3-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.
tags: extra sharp New York State cheese

title: refrigerator buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and sugar. Add beaten eggs, buttermilk and vegetable oil.
This mixture will refrigerate for 1 week.
You may add milk to thin.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes into bite size pieces.
Dice the onion.
Put in a pan and add water to cover the potatoes.
Add the bacon grease and cook all until tender.
Stir in cream of celery soup.

title: surprise cake
directions: Cream together butter or margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add the dry ingredients to creamed mixture, alternately with water and vanilla.
Beat well, then stir in sauerkraut.
Bake in two (8-inch) layer pans, or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass pan at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost as desired.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Grease 4 x 8-inch round cake pans or 1 (10 x 20-inch) pan, warm butter until it flows.
In large mixing bowl, mix butter and sugar with beater at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour 1 cup at a time until well mixed.
Pat evenly in pan or pans with hands.
Prick dough with fork all over. Bake 1 hour or until pale and golden, do not brown.
Cool in pans.

title: 24 hour cheese cake
directions: Mix jello and hot water; let cool.
In the meantime, mix crushed crackers with melted butter and powdered sugar.
Pat crumbs into 9 x 13-inch pan for crust.
You may reserve some crumbs for top.
Next cream the cream cheese, vanilla and sugar; set aside.
In a separate glass bowl, whip evaporated milk.
Milk must have been refrigerated and very cold.
Add jello mixture and cream cheese mixture to whipped milk.
Pour mixture over crust. Sprinkle any reserved crumbs over top.
Chill 24 hours.
Cut and serve.

title: brunch cake
directions: Mix 1 cup of the flour with the sugar and salt. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Set aside 1/2 cup of this mix for top. To remaining crumbs, add the other cup of flour sifted with baking powder and soda. Add buttermilk, egg and vanilla; blend thoroughly on low speed with mixer. Beat 1 minute more on medium speed. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Add cinnamon to crumb mixture reserved for topping. Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together.
Melt margarine and chocolate; add to egg mixture and mix well.
Add flour and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy chili with salsa(low fat)
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes and then serve.
Makes 8 cups.

title: jan's breakfast dish
directions: Microwave cream cheese until soft.
Cut bell peppers, mushrooms, and ham into small pieces.
Beat eggs slightly.
Mix eggs, cream cheese and chopped ingredients together.
Spray pie pan with vegetable spray.
Pour mixture into pie pie.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy herb bread
directions: Thaw bread dough and divide into 12 pieces.
Mix garlic in butter in a small bowl and mix cheese and herbs in another bowl. Dip pieces of dough in garlic mix, then in cheese mix and place in a 12-cup Bundt pan.
Cover lightly and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven until crust is golden and bread sounds hollow when tapped.
Serve warm.

title: shirley's vegetable tortillas
directions: Put small amount of water in frying pan; add a little salt. Bring to a boil and add vegetables.
Cover and cook until just tender; remove lid and cook a brief time to cook out any remaining water.
In flat pan, beat butter and place tortilla shell on it. On one side of tortilla place several cheese strips.
Place sauteed vegetables on top of cheese.
Spread lettuce on top of other vegetables.
Fold over the other side of tortilla and heat both sides.
This makes 2 to 3 tortillas.

title: carob nut cookies(slimming down cookbook)
directions: Cream egg, honey and oil until creamy.
Add flour, wheat germ and other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Add chips, raisins and nuts and mix well, being sure that the mixture is of stiff consistency.
Makes about 48 cookies.
Bake in 350° oven for about 8 to 9 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and shortenings.
Add vanilla, beaten egg and dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: red, white and blue delight
directions: Dissolve 1 package raspberry Jell-O in 2 cups hot water.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Soften unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Place sugar and half and half in saucepan. Bring to boiling point.
Remove from heat.
Add softened gelatin and cream cheese.
Beat at low speed until smooth.
Add almonds. Let cool.
Pour over firm raspberry layer.
Chill until firm. Dissolve remaining raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add blueberries and juice.
Let cool.
Pour over cheese layer.
Chill until firm.

title: new potatoes with lemon butter
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Pare a strip of skin, about 1/2-inch wide, around center of each potato.
Place potatoes in medium saucepan. Add boiling water to measure 2 inches and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Bring to boiling; boil gently, covered, for 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Return to heat for several minutes to dry out. Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Stir in lemon juice, snipped chives and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Pour over potatoes, turning to coat well.
Turn into serving dish.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Place in 9 x 13 (greased lightly) pan. Top with bacon and olives. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Can be made a day ahead. Can add additional cheese, too.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Dutch oven works best.
Saute oil, onion, meat and green pepper.
Stir in cream of chicken and milk.
Boil.
Place baking powder biscuits on top and bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and shape into small balls. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pink stuff
directions: Combine all ingredients in a serving bowl.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: kidney bean relish
directions: Put beans in strainer.
Rinse under cold water very quickly. Let drain.
Mix other ingredients.
Combine with beans. Refrigerate covered.
Serve on crackers.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Spread 1 can crescent rolls in a buttered casserole dish. Press cream cheese onto this. Spread pie filling over cream cheese. Top with other can of crescent rolls. Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: cabbage, cauliflower casserole
directions: Boil cabbage and cauliflower until cabbage is tender, then drain.
Make White Sauce.
Combine melted butter and flour. Gradually add milk and stir over heat until thickened.
Pour White Sauce over layered cabbage, cauliflower, bread crumbs and cheese. Garnish with parsley flakes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine first four ingredients in large bowl.
Blend in pieces of bread.
Pour mixture into 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until set.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Steam celery and onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together; top with cornflake crumbs.
Pour 1/2 stick melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Note: I double this recipe.

title: governor's potato casserole
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Fold in potatoes.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with shredded cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: chile cheese squares
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix eggs well.
Add cumin.
Add both kinds of cheese.
Line bottom of pan with green chilies.
Pour egg mixture over chilies.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until eggs are set.
When cooled five minutes, cut into squares.
Good brunch menu item!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a large casserole dish. Bake at 400° for about 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: *Omit baking powder and salt if using self-rising flour.

title: cream caramels
directions: Bring the ingredients to a boil, stirring constantly. Then stir in gradually 1 more cup of cream. Stir frequently as mixture begins to thicken, constantly as it darkens. Cook to 254° (a little dropped into cold water forms a hard ball). Pour into buttered 7-inch square pan with 1/2 cup chopped nuts scattered over the bottom. When cold, cut into squares.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Cook and stir hamburger until brown, then drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.

title: tex-mex casserole
directions: Combine ground turkey or beef, onion and 1/3 taco seasoning in skillet.
Cook until browned.
Stir in salsa and sour cream.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: In large mixing bowl beat together cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk until fluffy.
Slowly add lemon juice and blend well. Pour into graham cracker crust and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with chilled pie filling and serve.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by small teaspoonfuls and place a pecan half in each. Bake 9 to 10 minutes at 400°. Yield: 3 1/2 dozen.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in a Pyrex dish.
Place in freezer until frozen solid.

title: pirozhki(russian)
directions: DOUGH:
Mix warm milk with yeast, add salt and sugar, and 3 cups flour, 1 cup at a time.
Beat eggs in a bowl, stir eggs into mixture, warm up butter, stir into dough, add 1 Tbsp of vegetable oil.
Mix about 15 minutes, if dough seems liquid, add a little bit more flour.
Put dough into a big pot and cover.
Keep it in a warm place for 5 hours.

title: five can soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Heat thoroughly and serve with thick crusty bread.

title: butter toffee popcorn
directions: Heat oven to 225°.
Place popcorn in oven to keep warm.
Cook in heavy saucepan the butter and sugar until it reaches hard crack stage or 300° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over corn; toss until evenly coated.
Spread on cookie sheets to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Heat cheese, margarine, chocolate and corn syrup in 3-quart saucepan over medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture is melted.
Gradually add sugar to chocolate mixture, beating with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Smooth surface with spatula.
Cover and refrigerate several hours. Cut into squares.

title: mom's banana oatmeal bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with 1 tablespoon margarine.
In a large bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in oatmeal and set aside.
In a blender, combine eggs, margarine, buttermilk, lemon juice and sugar; process until smooth.
Add banana and nuts; process briefly.
Pour mixture into dry ingredients and mix until flour is moistened.
Pour into greased pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on rack after removing from pan.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: english muffin hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on English muffin halves and freeze briefly, then cut muffins into 4 wedges.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes if frozen; 6 to 8 minutes if not frozen.
Makes approximately 6 dozen wedges.

title: prehistoric dinosaur punch
directions: In a punch bowl, stir together grape juice and lemonade.
Add ginger ale and serve immediately.
Makes about 6 3/4 cups.

title: louisiana jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage in heavy Dutch oven.
Remove.
Add flour to sausage drippings.
Brown flour to a dark roux.
Add onions, parsley and garlic.
Cook until soft, then add water and rice, salt and pepper and browned sausage.
When it comes to a boil, lower heat to lowest point and cook for about 1 hour, covered tightly.
When rice is done, remove lid and let cook for a few minutes until rice dries a little.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange snowballs
directions: Mix crumbs, melted margarine, 1 cup powdered sugar, nuts, orange juice and Grand Marnier.
Shape into small balls.
Mix soft margarine and remaining powdered sugar; add enough milk for spreading consistency.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Put popped corn in brown grocery bag or big bowl. In a separate bowl, put sugar, butter, corn syrup, and salt. Microwave 1 to 2 minutes, until bubbly. Stir. Boil 3 minutes in microwave; stirring after each minute. Add baking soda and vanilla. Stir. Pour mixture over popped corn (in brown bag or in large bowl). Shake or stir. Microwave 1 minute then shake/stir. Microwave 30 seconds, then shake/stir. Microwaveone more time for 30 seconds, then shake/stir. Spread on cookie sheet to cool.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until blended.
Blend in melted butter, stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.
Makes one 9-inch pie.
Recipe may be doubled.
Bake two pies; freeze one for later.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in pie crust.
Chill well before serving.

title: caramel pie
directions: Bake both crusts and let cool.
Brown margarine, coconut and pecans.
Set aside to cool.
Mix cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Take Cool Whip and fold into cream cheese and Eagle Brand mixture.
Take 1/4 of cream cheese mixture and place into a pie crust, then sprinkle nut mixture on top and pour 1/4 of caramel topping.
Repeat with second layer of cream cheese mixture, nut mixture and caramel.
After finishing second layer, place in freezer.
Best eaten when cold and firm.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread and spread with butter.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Brown sausage; drain well and spoon over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs with milk and salt.
Mix well and pour over cheese; chill overnight.
Remove from refrigerator a while before baking at 300° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Pour 1/4 of batter into bread pans, sprinkle with brown sugar mixture; repeat until gone.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Then mix vegetables, ground beef and soup in 2-quart casserole dish.
Place cheese on top of mix.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; peel while warm.
Salt and pepper.
Fry bacon; crumble.
Add all ingredients to potatoes.
Saute onion.
Add a little vinegar and egg in the bacon grease.
Stir until this thickens.
Pour over potatoes.

title: recipe for holiday scent
directions: Mix 1/2 cup vinegar and 1 gallon water in a pail.
Pour into spray bottles for convenience.

title: prune cake deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a stem cake pan.
Cook at 350° until done.
Punch holes in cake with a fork.
Pour sauce over cake while hot.

title: crabmeat muffins
directions: Blend margarine and cheese together at room temperature.
Add onion and Tabasco sauce; mix well.
Add crabmeat, well drained. Refrigerate for 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Split English muffins and spread with a small amount of margarine.
Toast.
Spread mixture on muffins and broil.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Mix together milk, flour, eggs and sugar and set aside.
Fry apple slices in butter in round cake pan.
Butter pan on sides after apple is fried and pour batter over apple.
Bake in 500° oven until batter rises and starts to brown, about 10 minutes. Dot with butter and sprinkle thickly with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Put back in oven to melt and brown.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.

title: low-fat twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until tender (45 to 50 minutes).
Cool slightly; cut in half lengthwise and gently scoop out each potato half, leaving a thin shell.
Put pulp in small bowl; add cheese, chives, basil, salt and pepper.
Beat until smooth.
Add milk a tablespoon at a time until fluffy.
Spoon or pipe into shells.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place on baking sheet.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 more minutes or until heated through.

title: spinach balls
directions: Squeeze all water out of uncooked spinach.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Form into balls (golf ball size).
Place on a cookie sheet and place in freezer.

title: tuna and biscuits
directions: Brown onion and green peppers in hot oil.
Add flour and blend.
Add soup and milk; cook until sauce is thick and smooth. Add flaked tuna and lemon juice.
Pour into a greased baking dish. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 425°. Cover casserole with biscuits.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until biscuits are browned.

title: peanut butter wheels candy
directions: Mix together.
Roll on waxed paper, thin.
Spread a thin layer of peanut butter on top and roll up.
Chill, slice and serve.

title: savory wild rice casserole
directions: Pour 4 cups boiling water over rice; let stand 15 minutes and drain.
Stir in soups, mushrooms with liquid, bouillon cubes, 1 cup water, bay leaf and seasonings.
Saute celery and onion in butter until transparent.
Add to rice mixture.

title: big soft ginger cookies
directions: Combine flour, ginger, soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt. Set aside.

title: salad
directions: Mix well.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours in the refrigerator before serving.

title: *emma warfield's salad dressing
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Add vinegar and water gradually until well blended, then add eggs.
Place in a double boiler and stir until thick.
Add butter and mustard.

title: peach (or mango) bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in bowl.
Mix well; combine eggs, oil, vanilla, fruit, raisins and nuts.
Mix into dry ingredients.
Grease bread pan; pour batter into pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put rice on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour combined soups over rice.
Put chicken parts on top.
Sprinkle Lipton onion soup over all.
Dissolve beef bouillon in 1 cup hot water and pour over top, then add cooking sherry.
Bake, covered, 1 hour and uncovered, 15 minutes at 350°.

title: oven kahlua pork
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Rub over pork.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with aluminum foil, allowing foil to extend generously over one end.
Place pork on foil.
Fold foil over the pork, sealing well.
Roast in 325° oven 4 hours.
To serve:
Shred with 2 forks or with fingers instead of carving.

title: fire and ice
directions: Mix together and serve over cream cheese with crackers.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Defrost potatoes.
Mix butter, salt, pepper, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and a couple of slices of butter.
Bake 30 minutes or until everything is done and melted.

title: easy lemonade pie
directions: Mix together lemonade and milk.
Fold in whipped topping. Place in graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: chess squares
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add cake mix and 1 egg, slightly beaten.
Mix with a fork and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Mix 2 eggs, beaten, with cream cheese (room temperature) until creamy.
Add powdered sugar and mix for 5 minutes.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. (I usually bake mine a few minutes longer.)
Cool and cut into squares.

title: butter cookies
directions: Save egg whites for brushing tops.

title: plantation almond tea
directions: In teapot, place sugar, lemon juice and tea bags.
Pour boiling water over tea mixture.
Cover.
Let steep for 10 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add remaining ingredients except ice.
Stir.
Serve over ice cubes.
If desired, garnish with lemon slices.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: jean's pinwheel cookies
directions: Cream butter (oleo) and sugar.
Add egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Knead until smooth and roll 1/2-inch thick.
Spread with filling.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix well and pour into a graham cracker pie crust.
Cool for 24 hours.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Place apples in bottom of greased casserole.
Sprinkle cranberries over apples.
Mix oatmeal and sugar.
Pour over cranberries.
Combine margarine, brown sugar, flour and nuts. Spread over oatmeal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: beef and peppers for two
directions: In a bowl stir together soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch, flavor enhancer, salt, ginger and pepper.
Pour over sliced steak and let marinate 10 minutes.
Over medium heat in a skillet, heat vegetable oil.
Add meat and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add sliced onion, green pepper and tomato.
Cover and simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or sheet cake pan.

title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl and mix well.
Pour onto hot greased griddle.
Brown both sides of cakes, turning only once.
Serve with maple syrup.
Makes 12 medium cakes.

title: old-fashioned lemonade
directions: Wash lemons and slice thin.
Place in 1 gallon pitcher.
Add sugar.
Pound with a wooden spoon to squeeze juice from slices. Stir well.
Add several ice cubes.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Add water to make 1 gallon.
Serve the same day as made.

title: pickled bologna
directions: Cut ring bologna in 1 to 1 1/2-inch slices.
Fill 2-quart (or larger) jar with all ingredients.
Let stand 2 days before using. Will keep several days.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions, garlic and mushrooms in butter.
Add chili powder, broth, tomatoes and cheese.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Add chicken and spaghetti.
If possible, refrigerate overnight.
(This is not crucial, but it really is good if you can include this step.)

title: easy chicken cordon bleu
directions: Have
chicken
breasts skinned, boned and split.
Use 2 slices of
ham
and
cheese for each piece of chicken.
Pound each piece
chicken
to 1/8-inch thickness.
On each piece of chicken, place
ham
and cheese and roll.
Coat with Shake 'n Bake.
Fasten with
toothpick.
Bake
in ungreased pan for 20 minutes at 400°. Dilute soup; heat and pour over chicken.

title: pelf's corn fritters(american)
directions: Combine pancake mix, sugar, milk, oil and egg in a bowl.
Add creamed corn until mixture is a semi-thick consistency.
Mix very well.
Melt 1 stick margarine in a 12-inch skillet.
On medium-high heat, drop in heaping tablespoonfuls of mix.
Cook, turning frequently, until golden brown.
Fill the bottom of a plate with grenadine or honey.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and serve. Preparation time:
30 minutes.
Cooking time:
20 minutes.

title: quick coconut pie
directions: Mix together coconut and milk; set aside.
Melt margarine. Mix together margarine, sugar, beaten eggs, vanilla and lemon, then add coconut mixture.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: old virginia grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except eggs.
Just before pouring into buttered baking dish, add beaten eggs.
Stir well.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Combine crushed wafers with butter and cinnamon.
Press into bottom and sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.

title: salted nut roll
directions: Heat the Eagle Brand milk, peanut butter chips and margarine until chips are melted.
Stir in the miniature marshmallows; heat 40 seconds.
Stir; heat 40 seconds.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer as follows:
1/2 peanuts, melted mixture and remaining 1/2 peanuts.
Lightly press peanuts into mixture.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into 6 to 8 squares or wedges.
Cover with water and add 1 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon butter.
Bring to boil for 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain cabbage.
Beat eggs and 4 tablespoons milk. In another container mix flour, pepper and remaining salt.
Dip cabbage into egg mixture and coat with flour.
Deep fry in hot bacon dripping.
May also be pan-fried.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick tea sandwiches
directions: Alternate, starting with bread, then ham, then pumpernickel or rye, then cheese, white bread, chicken and wheat bread.
The amount of spread needed depends on the amount you spread.
Some bakeries will "color" bread if you ask.
You can trim ends before spreading and cut in triangle shapes or use cookie cutters.
Use long toothpicks to keep sandwiches together.
May garnish with olives.

title: meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Press into a loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing. Makes 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Make white sauce in double boiler by melting margarine; stir in flour, then add Pet milk, stirring constantly, until thickened. In medium casserole dish, pour white sauce over squash and onions.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cream frosting
directions: Melt morsels and combine with the rest of the ingredients. Garnish with coconut.

title: sweet spice nuts
directions: In 2-quart casserole, combine sugar, water, salt, cinnamon, allspice, cloves and nutmeg.
Cook on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until sugar is melted.
Stir in nuts.
Cook on High 4 to 5 minutes or until syrup begins to harden.
Immediately pour nut mixture onto buttered cookie sheet.
Spread thinly.
Cool.
Break into small pieces.

title: chocolate trifle(serves 12 to 14 people)
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package; let cool.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Crush up Skor bars into small pieces.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Break up sausage into small pieces.
Brown in skillet and drain grease.
Do the same with hamburger.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients into bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll out on floured surface; cut with biscuit cutter.
Place in casserole.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or longer or until browned.
Yields 4 servings.

title: westernburger skillet
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender (use shortening if necessary).
Stir to separate meat; pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients.
Heat; stir occasionally.
Garnish with cooked bacon if desired.

title: #2 cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order and pour in medium size skillet or cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Resembles pound cake.

title: ryna banana oat pecan bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in a medium bowl.
Slice bananas and beat with mixer until pureed.
Add eggs, sugar and oil; beat until blended.
Stir in flour mixture until moistened.
Add oats and pecans.
Turn in prepared loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly mix together the brown sugar, salt, flour and spices.
Add slightly beaten eggs and pumpkin; mix well until blended.
Stir in milk and water; pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 20 minutes longer, until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, milk and soups; place in baking dish.
Place uncooked chicken breasts on top of mixture.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until chicken is fully cooked.

title: "baked eggs"
directions: Cube bread small. Put in bottom of well-greased pans. Mix eggs, milk, salt, dry mustard and pepper. Pour over bread. Place ham and cheese on top. Foil and refrigerate overnight. Leave foil on and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Check 1/2 hour.

title: dilled fried potatoes
directions: Boil unpeeled potatoes in salted water.
Add a clove of garlic to water.
Cool, peel and cut potatoes into large cubes.
Slice onions and fry in oil until lightly browned, then add potatoes, salt and pepper and fry until warmed through and browned. Sprinkle with finely minced dill and serve.

title: apple dip
directions: Boil 2 or 3 eggs more than needed to allow for breakage.
boil for 10 minutes.
Rinse in cold water.
Leave in water and peel off shells while warm.

title: asparagus chinese style
directions: Cut asparagus in diagonal pieces and cook a few minutes in 2 tablespoons oil.
(Can add chicken breasts.)
If you add cubed pieces of chicken, after stir-frying the asparagus, remove with a slotted spoon and brown chicken in oil.
Then add asparagus, sherry, soy sauce, chicken broth and cornstarch.
Stir and cook a few minutes until chicken is done and asparagus is tender.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Don't overbake.
Put wax paper in the bottom of tube pan.
Grease and flour pan well.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat egg, milk and salad oil.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend well.
Stir in corn.
Drop batter from spoon into a hot greased frypan.
Brown both sides.

title: venison summer sausage
directions: Mix all well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Mix well every day for 3 days.

title: date pudding
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 9-inch or 8 x 8-inch pan. Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: banana nut fruit cake
directions: Mix together bananas, sliced butter, oil and eggs.
Beat by hand.
There will be lumps of butter and bananas.
Mix flour, sugar, cloves, cinnamon, allspice and soda in a paper bag.
Do not sift.
Combine the two mixtures.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in loaf pans, lined with wax paper in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Cool, remove from pan and remove wax paper.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Cook brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove, add soda and stir.
Mix into popcorn. Spread coated popcorn on cookie sheet.
Place in 200 degree oven for 1 hour stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: texas eggs
directions: Beat eggs with milk.
Melt butter in skillet.
Scramble eggs. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with bacon, peppers, onions and mushrooms.
Warm soup with sherry (or water).
Spread over top. Top with grated cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 250° for 50 minutes.

title: mango bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Make a well.
Mix and add sugar, oil, vanilla, mango, eggs, raisins and nuts into the well of dry ingredients.
Mix and pour into a well-greased loaf pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) and let it stand for 20 minutes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: avocado soup
directions: Sprinkle avocados with a little lemon juice on each piece. Place in blender or food processor.
Add the onion, sour cream, buttermilk and salt; process.
Add broth; if too thick, add more broth.
Serve cold in small cups.

title: easy pecan rolls
directions: Place frozen rolls into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding, sugar, nuts and cinnamon. Sprinkle over rolls.
Melt margarine and pour over all. Cover with greased waxed paper.
Place in cold oven overnight.
In the morning, remove rolls.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Invert pan and serve.

title: backpack jerky
directions: Slice meat along the grain 1/4-inch thick. Heat both sauces, then add all other ingredients. Cool and add meat. Marinate overnight. Next day, put meat directly over oven racks. Put oven on lowest heat settings and leave door open, approximately 4 to 6 hours.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and raisins. Add sugar, shortening, salt and molasses. Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast dissolved in 1/2 cup lukewarm water. Add 5 cups flour and beat well. Add 5 more cups of flour.
Knead well.
Let rise until double.
Knead down.
Let rise again, then put in tins and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Stir in milk and cheese; blend.
Cook noodles.
Add noodles, corn, soup and pimentos to beef.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy corn spread
directions: Mix together.
Serve with crackers or carrot and celery sticks. May be frozen.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine Veg-All, onion, sour cream and soup.
Add 1/2 stack crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix remaining crushed Ritz crackers with melted margarine.
Spread evenly over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Cream butter and	sugars, beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, and salt, add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield approximately 4 dozen.

title: roast turkey, italian
directions: Rub turkey breast with half of olive oil, then rub garlic salt and pepper over.
Separate skin from breast, but do not remove skin!!
Mix remaining olive oil and herbs together, then rub mixture underneath skin.
Press skin back into place.
Squeeze lemon inside of turkey cavity.
Place turkey on a rack in uncovered roasting pan in a 325° preheated oven.
Baste every 20 minutes.
Turkey is done when juices are clear.
For a pretty turkey, place four pineapple rings, one behind the other, secure with toothpicks.
With a toothpick, secure one cherry in the middle of pineapple rings.
Serves 6.

title: honey-walnut dressing(for fresh spinach)
directions: Combine oil and mustard with a wire whisk; stir in vinegar and water.
Add honey, whisking until blended.
Add nuts.
Cover and chill.

title: pasta pie
directions: Precook rigatoni.
Brown meat with onion, green pepper and garlic.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato paste, spaghetti sauce, sugar and oregano.
Heat thoroughly (mixture will thicken).
Grease 9-inch pie pan well.
Beat eggs; add melted butter and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Pour pasta (cooked, drained and cooled) into pie pan.
Pour egg mixture over and mix in thoroughly.
Pour sauce mixture over all.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top and serve.

title: mediterranean bouillabaisse
directions: In Dutch oven or large saucepan, cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add tomatoes, clam juice, wine, parsley, salt, thyme, bay leaf and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally to break up tomatoes.
Add shrimp, fish, scallops and crab legs.
Cook 5 minutes longer or until fish flakes with fork.
Add clams.
Season to taste with Old Bay seafood seasoning.
Heat through.
Serve over cooked white rice.

title: sausage cheese rolls
directions: Cook sausage; break into small pieces and drain.
Add Cheez Whiz and stir until combined.
Split rolls into halves, lengthwise; spread mixture on the center of the rolls.
Cover with foil; heat in a slow oven until heated (at 300° for about 20 minutes).

title: rock candy
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in large saucepan.
Stir over medium heat, boiling for 5 minutes.
Test in a cup of cold water until it threads.
Remove from heat, then add color and flavor.
Grease pan with butter and pour candy into pan.
Let cool and then break into pieces.

title: creamed eggs on toast
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk, stir until sauce boils and thickens.
Then add sliced hard cooked eggs and asparagus. Serve on toast.

title: spumoni cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, vanilla and egg; stir in flour and salt. Divide in 3 parts.
Mix nuts and green color in one, melted chocolate in one and cherries in last.
Line bottom and ends of loaf pan with aluminum foil.
Press nut dough in bottom, then chocolate dough on top of nut dough, then cherry.
Cover dough with extended end of foil.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Remove dough and cut into 1/4-inch slices and then each slice crosswise in half.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pfeffernuesse cookies
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, citron and nuts (chopped fine).
Dissolve soda in sour milk.
Add with flour in which cinnamon has been sifted.
Roll in small balls.
Bake at 325° until light brown.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cook potatoes for 12 to 15 minutes; drain and mash.
Measure 1 cup potatoes; cool.
Beat sugar, margarine and vanilla until combined.
Add egg yolks, one at a time; beat after each egg.
Add potatoes; mix well.
In a separate bowl, mix the flour, cocoa and baking powder; add to potato mixture alternately with milk.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into flour mixture.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes; invert pan. Serves 10.

title: old-fashioned rice pudding(microwave, serves 6 to 8)
directions: In microwaveproof 2-quart casserole or baking dish, mix together eggs, milk, sugar and salt.
Stir in rice, raisins and vanilla.
Cook uncovered on High, 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir every 1 to 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg and let stand about 30 minutes, without stirring.
Serve warm or cold.
After trying both the cinnamon and the nutmeg, I found the nutmeg to be the better of the two.

title: italian stuffed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out dough in rectangle.
Paint with egg (scramble it.)
Lay spinach on egged dough.
Place pepperoni; sprinkle with cheese.
Roll into loaf.
Place on cookie sheet.
Paint top with melted butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 28 to 30 minutes.

title: bell pepper casserole
directions: Line bottom of a 7 1/2 x 11-inch Pyrex dish with bell peppers which have been cut into quarters and boiled for 5 minutes.
Brown hamburger meat, salt, pepper, onion and chopped bell pepper. Drain off grease.
Add tomatoes, water and rice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, until rice is tender.
Add grated cheese.
Pour over bell peppers in Pyrex dish.
Cover with grated cheese and bake, covered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(May be baked in microwave for about 10 minutes, if desired.)

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash potatoes.
Slice about 1/4-inch thick.
Place in 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with seasonings. Drizzle with melted margarine.
Pour dressing over potatoes. Toss to coat well.
Cover.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until tender. Yield:
8 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Make the day before serving.
Cook pasta; drain and rinse well with cold water.
In a large bowl, mix the next four ingredients. Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Toss in pasta and mix well. Cover and refrigerate.

title: out-of-this-world cheesy pretzels(children's)
directions: Combine baking mix, milk and cheese in a bowl and mix well. Roll into 8 x 12-inch rectangle on floured surface.
Cut into strips.
Twist each strip into a pretzel shape and place on greased baking sheet.
Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with salt. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat margarine and cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sugar. Add eggs, and beat well.
Blend in flour and flavoring.
Pour in tube pan.
Place in cold oven, and turn to 350 degrees, and bake 2 1/2 hours.

title: cherry cheese jell-o salad
directions: Add enough water to reserved juice to equal 1 cup, add sugar; bring to a boil.
Add Jell-O and pineapple; partially congeal. Whip, add cheese and gently fold in Cool Whip.

title: easy beef stew(serves 4)
directions: Put meat in bottom of casserole. On top, add 1 sliced onion, carrots, celery and potatoes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper if desired. Add tomato juice and wine. Cover and put in 300° oven for 2 hours. Correct seasoning. Cook 2 more hours. You may have to add more liquid. Check on it.

title: oven baked hamburgers with gravy
directions: Mix 2 cups water and soup mix and put into oblong baking dish. Form meat into patties and place in dish.
Add onion slices.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes depending on size of patties.
Mix flour and 4 tablespoons water with fork until well blended.
Put into dish with patties, mixing well with gravy mixture to thicken.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together sweetened condensed milk, vanilla pudding and water. Beat well.
Set in refrigerator for 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer mixture, bananas, then wafers.
Continue to layer. Chill in refrigerator.

title: bacon tomato cups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coarsely chop bacon, tomato and onion in food chopper.
Grate cheese and mix all together, except biscuits. Set aside.
Separate each biscuit into 3 thinner biscuits and lay over mini muffin cup.
Using mini tart press dipped in flour, press each biscuit into cup.
Fill with bacon mixture.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes 30 appetizers.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots, green pepper and salt in large metal mixing bowl.
Cover and let stand 2 hours.
Drain.
Pour dressing over cabbage mixture, cover and freeze.
Slice and serve.

title: 5 minute fudge
directions: Boil together sugar and milk for 5 minutes, stirring so it doesn't scorch.
Remove from stove and add chocolate chips, marshmallows and vanilla and blend well.
Add nuts.
Place in a buttered pan and allow to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: banana nugget cookies
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg, bananas, oatmeal and chocolate bits. Drop with a spoon on a very little greased pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: stuffed pistolette rolls
directions: Cut off ends of rolls and save.
Hollow out middle of rolls. Brown hamburger meat and sausage.
Melt cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Stuff rolls and put ends back on.
Roll in butter and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: three seafood casserole
directions: In large pot of boiling salted water, cook macaroni until tender, but still firm, 6 to 8 minutes; drain.

title: vegetables italiano
directions: In plastic food bag, combine crumbs and Parmesan; shake to blend well.
In another bag, combine mayonnaise and vegetables; shake to coat well.
Add mayonnaise-coated vegetables, half at a time, to crumb mixture; shake to coat well.
Arrange in a single layer on ungreased cookie sheet so that pieces do not touch.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes, or until golden.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: sugar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In pie shell, mix flour and sugar with fork.
Gradually add milk, making sure to break any clumps of sugar mixture.
Slice butter into 6 pats and float on top of milk. Sprinkle top with cinnamon (approximately 1 teaspoon).
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°; bake until firm (approximately 25 minutes).
Times may vary.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins with water and cook about 20 minutes; add white sugar and cook a few minutes longer.
Add cinnamon, butter and molasses; mix well.
Bake in raw pie crust.
Put lattice pie crust on top.
Sprinkle a little white sugar on top of lattice and bake in 425° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
I sprinkle a little flour in the bottom of pie crust before I put raisin mixture in raw crust.

title: pepper hash
directions: Add peppers and onions to boiling water; cover and let stand 25 minutes. Drain and add remaining ingredients; boil 15 minutes. Seal while hot in sterilized jars.

title: fried zucchini with onions
directions: In a heavy skillet, melt margarine.
Lightly saute onion slices.
Wash zucchini; slice in thin rounds, leaving skin on. Add to onions and salt and pepper.
Fry over low heat, turning as slices brown.
Add water and low heat.
Cover tightly and steam for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Serves 4.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Dip pieces in milk; coat with flour.
Dip in egg and coat again with flour.
Place in a skillet and cook until golden brown.

title: quick pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown the ground beef and drain well. Press 2 cans of biscuits on a greased cookie sheet to the thickness you desire for pizza crust.
Place biscuits in oven for 5 minutes; remove cookie sheet from oven and spread browned meat on crust. Salt and pepper.
Pour tomato sauce over the meat.
Mix Parmesan cheese and milk together and pour over top of pizza.
Sprinkle oregano over the top and bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fudge nougats
directions: Combine in saucepan 2 cups sugar, butter and evaporated milk. Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in morsels, flour, graham crackers, walnuts and vanilla.
Spread in well-buttered 12 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: baked tarragon chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wash and wipe chicken dry.
Carefully loosen skin from breast and thighs and legs.
Stuff skin carefully.
Tie well.
Bake in small container, adding 1 cup chicken bouillon.
Baste with part of butter.

title: baked ham and eggs
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer hash browns on bottom. Put on layer of ham.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter, then pour over ham layer.
Mix salt, eggs and milk and pour over ham mixture.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
(Great brunch or company dish.)

title: bacon or sausage quiche
directions: Mix ingredients except croutons and cheese. Line greased 9 x 13 casserole with croutons. Sprinkle cheese over croutons. Pour mix over croutons and cheese. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Heat oil; add beef and cook until brown.
Add garlic and vegetables and cook until tender.
Drain grease and add soy sauce to mixture.
Add cornstarch (dry) mixed with water to hot mixture. Stir and cook until thick.
Serve over rice.

title: strawberry twinkie cake
directions: Slice berries in half and set aside. Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with Twinkies sliced in half. Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and milk with a mixer. Add to pan on top of Twinkies. Top with glaze. Top with berries. Keep in the refrigerator.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Add marshmallows. Let cool until it begins to thicken. Add other ingredients. Fold in. Refrigerate until firm.

title: poppy seed fruit salad
directions: Combine cornstarch and apple juice in pan, stirring well over medium heat.
Pour into small bowl.
Add dressing oil and poppy seed.
Cool.
Combine fruit in large bowl.
Add liquid and toss. Cover and chill.
Add bananas before serving.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and garlic in hot fat.
Add tomato paste, canned tomatoes, salt, oregano and pepper.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles according to directions.
In an oblong baking dish (7 x 11-inch) alternate layers of cooked noodles, Swiss cheese, cottage cheese and meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan; add onion slices.
Cook until tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Put onions in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over onions and layer with cheese.
Arrange bread slices on top; brush with butter, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and lightly grease baking sheets. Combine flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream sugar, butter or margarine and shortening. Beat in eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour mixture just until blended.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on baking sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes or until set around edges. Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: mushroom stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms with a damp cloth, remove stems and reserve caps.
Finely chop stems to make about 2 cups.
Saute in butter with onion in a large skillet.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add cream and cook, stirring, until thick.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Top with bacon bits, if desired.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Drain clams, reserving liquor.
Fry salt pork until crisp in large saucepan; remove.
Add water, potatoes, onion and reserved clam liquor to fat in saucepan.
Cook covered until potatoes are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add milk, cream, clams and salt pork. Heat slowly just to boiling.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Float butter atop each serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ken's potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs and potatoes, in a bowl.
Let stand at least 10 minutes to let flavors mingle.
Mix in eggs that have been sliced or chunked and the potatoes.

title: 5 in 1 dish
directions: Place hamburger in bottom of greased casserole.
Cover with layer of potatoes, then vegetables which have been cooked. Pour tomatoes over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix together and serve with nacho chips, Tostitos, bagel chips or wheat crackers.

title: scaloppine marinara al pecorino romano
directions: In a saute pan, over medium heat, heat 3 tablespoons of the olive oil and saute the garlic.
(Be careful not to let the garlic turn brown.)
Add the tomatoes, salt, pepper and the oregano. Turn up the heat and cook for 4 minutes.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins and water 15 minutes.
Drain juice to 1 cup. Flour raisins.
Beat all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: best ever lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together in top of double boiler.
Add water.
Combine egg yolks with juice and beat well.
Add to the rest of the mix.
Cook until thick over boiling water for 25 minutes.
Add lemon extract and vinegar and stir.
Pour into pan and cool.
Cover with meringue and brown in oven for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: golden raisin nut bread
directions: Let stand overnight or until cooled the raisins, boiling water and soda.
Cream the sugar and shortening. Beat eggs into sugar mixture. Combine the raisin and sugar mixtures slowly.
Add the flour, salt, baking powder, vanilla and nut meats. Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in butter.
Add 2 cups water and Worcestershire sauce;
boil.

title: buttered biscuits
directions: First, get the size bowl you want and put a half stick of butter in it.
Put in microwave and melt.
Next, put the flour in bowl and put milk in.
Then stir until stuck together and knead the dough and roll with a rolling pin.
If you don't have a rolling pin, you can make drop biscuits.
Just put on a spoon and drop them in a pan.

title: sausage quiche
directions: In skillet, brown sausages until done.
Drain and cut into small pieces.
Place in the bottom of a pie shell.
Sprinkle with cheese.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs; add cream and nutmeg.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, oleo and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix with mixer sugar, eggs, oil, orange juice, flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix with spatula apples, pecans and coconut.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: marie's buttermilk rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together 2 cups flour and the yeast. Melt margarine, milk and sugar in a saucepan (about 120°).
Add to flour mixture.
Add egg and beat with electric mixer for 3 minutes. Using wooden spoon, stir in remaining flour, using as much as you can.

title: california bran muffins
directions: Combine Bran with boiling water and set aside. In large bowl beat together salt, margarine, sugar, eggs, and buttermilk. Mix flour, dry All Bran, and raisins. Add to first mixture. Bake in muffin cups about 23 minutes at 400.

title: creamy german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; drain.
Crumble and set aside.
Cook onions in bacon drippings until crisp.
Stir in sugar, flour, salt and celery seed; blend well.
Cook until mixture is smooth and bubbly; stir constantly.
Gradually add water and vinegar.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens.
Add potatoes and bacon; mix gently.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer over low heat for 25 to 30 minutes.
Gently stir in sour cream.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve hot.
Store any remaining in refrigerator.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Place butter in a 2-quart microwave-safe dish.
Microwave for 45 seconds to 1 1/2 minutes or until the butter has melted.
Mix in Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, salt, cinnamon, garlic powder and ground cloves.
Stir the pecans into the butter-spice mixture. Blend thoroughly.

Microwave, uncovered, for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes. When mixture has heated through, spread nuts on a paper towel to cool. When pecans have cooled, place in airtight containers. Store at room temperature.

title: easy fudge
directions: Put butter in bowl.
When the butter is soft, add the cocoa, dry milk, water and half of the sugar.
Mix together with a spoon. Add the rest of the sugar and mix again with the spoon.
Spread the fudge in a flat pan with a spatula.
Cool the fudge in the refrigerator for an hour.
Cut into squares and its ready to serve.

title: baked stuffed onions
directions: Peel whole onions and cook in salted water until just tender (20 to 25 minutes). Drain and cool. Scoop out center of onion, leaving several outside layers as shell. Chop centers of onions very fine. Cook bacon until crisp, then crumble. Combine chopped onions, chopped mushrooms, bread crumbs, bacon, salt, melted butter, 1/2 cup cheese and 2 Tbsp. parsley. Toss lightly. Fill onion shells. Place in greased baking pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and parsley just before serving. Serves 6.

title: no fail rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add sugar, salt, egg and shortening. Beat well. Add flour. Knead and let rise until double in bulk. Make into buns, rolls or coffee cakes. Let rise. Bake as usual, 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until they sound hollow.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat together until stiff the egg whites and baking powder. Add slowly the sugar, soda crackers and nuts.
Pour into greased pie pan (9 to 10-inch).
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool 1 to 2 hours.
Mix together Cool Whip and strawberries and fill crust.

title: brown candy
directions: Caramelize 1 cup sugar.
In large pan, boil 2 cups sugar and milk.
Pour caramelized sugar into boiling mixture in slow steady stream.
Cook to a steady stream.
Remove from heat; add soda, butter, cream, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until glossy appearance becomes dull.
Drop on wax paper and cool.

title: jello cookies
directions: Mix all together, chill 1 hour or overnight.
Shape into balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Store in airtight containers.

title: baby food cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Place in long cake pan and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill 2 hours.

title: waffles
directions: Keep whites of eggs for last and beat them until fluffy.
Mix remaining ingredients together by hand.
Fold beaten egg whites into batter gently.
Bake and enjoy.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Soak gelatin in water.
Scald milk.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Beat egg yolks.
Stir milk in slowly.
Stir in sugar mixture.
Cook over hot water about 20 minutes.
Take 1 cup custard.
Add to it 1 1/2 ounces chocolate.
Beat until well blended.
Add vanilla.
Pour in pie shell.
Dissolve gelatin in remaining hot custard.
Let cool, but not stiffen.
Stir in rum, egg white, salt, tartar and sugar.
Fold in egg whites in custard. Cover with whipped cream.

title: huckleberry slump
directions: Mix flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and 1 teaspoon salt together.
Cut in 1 tablespoon butter.
Stir in milk.
Set aside.

title: gazpacho
directions: Chop vegetables coarsely and add to tomato juice in blender. Pulse to chop finely.
Do in batches.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve in bowls with additional chopped vegetables for garnish.

title: quick treat
directions: Place graham crackers in single layer on a large cookie sheet. In double boiler, melt margarine and brown sugar together.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add nuts.
Pour this mixture over graham cookies. Bake in 300° oven for 10 minutes.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring the 1 cup sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat and add 1 1/2 cups peanut butter.
Add vanilla and stir well.
Pour over cereal; put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread on cooled bars.

title: vegie chili(light recipe)
directions: Praise our Lord everyday for all His blessings.
Love our neighbors as we love ourselves.
Treat everyone we meet as we would have them treat us.
And, before we criticize anyone else, let us walk just one mile in his shoes.
When we see someone down or depressed, a kind smile and a nice compliment may boost him or her for the day.
Taking all these phrases, blend with friendship and hope.
Preserve them in our hearts to serve daily with generous helpings of love and understanding.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: favorite holiday cake(peter paul mound cake)
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy and sugar is dissolved.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition of egg.
Combine flours together; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.

title: szechuan broccoli
directions: Combine soy sauce, vinegar and sugar in a small bowl; set aside.
Heat a large skillet or wok over medium heat.
Add sesame seed; cook 1 minute or until browned.
Remove seed and set aside.

title: taco salad(serves 20)
directions: Mix together onion, tomatoes, lettuce and cheese.
Add avocado.
Add beans, chips and hamburger just before serving so chips do not become soggy.

title: low-fat applesauce bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine cereal and milk.
Set aside.
In another bowl, combine egg, applesauce and melted margarine.
Stir into cereal mixture.
Add the dry ingredients.
Stir until just blended.
Spray muffin tin with nonstick cooking spray.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Contains 2.5 g fat per muffin.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix with a spoon and pour into a slightly greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oven-fried eggplant
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a shallow dish.
Peel eggplant and cut into 1/4-inch round slices.
Spread both sides of eggplant slices with mayonnaise.
Dredge in bread crumb mixture.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Grease bottom only of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.	Combine all ingredients
(except
chocolate
and
nuts) in large mixer bowl, blend well.
Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Pour into pan. Bake at 350°
for
1 hour.	Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan, cool on wire rack.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix softened margarine with flour until blended.
Add nuts. Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°. Mix softened cream cheese with sugar; fold in 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread on top cooled crust.
Mix pudding and 3 cups milk.
Spread on cream cheese mixture.
Spread rest of Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Chill.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add the flour and soda.
Add the oatmeal, coconut and gumdrops.
Mix well.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: black, white and red bean chili with sausage
directions: Heat olive oil.
Add sausages and brown, about 8 minutes. Remove.
Add onion and saute 5 minutes.
Add bell peppers and chilies and saute 1 minute.
Add chili powder and cumin.
Stir until aromatic, about 30 seconds.
Add tomatoes and beans.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cut sausage into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add to chili and simmer about 10 minutes.
Mix in vinegar.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve with Fontina, Corn and Jalapeno Quesadillas.
Freezes well.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Steam broccoli and drain.
Beat eggs and cheese together.
Add corn bread mix, margarine, onion and broccoli.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes in a large iron frying pan or 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat egg.
Mix together the sugar and flour or cornstarch. Add this to the egg.
