Add salt, creamed corn, milk and vanilla; stir thoroughly.
Put butter on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans. Cook at 350° for 1 hour (45 to 50 minutes, depending on oven).

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Wash and dry shrimp. Melt butter; stir in pepper, Worcestershire sauce and red pepper sauce. Place shrimp in shallow pan. Pour butter mixture over shrimp. Broil 3 minutes on 1 side; turn and broil 2 minutes on other side. Serves 4.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until tender; add broth, Cream of Chicken soup and melted cheese. Delicious served with corn bread.

title: cinnamon cocoa
directions: For beverage mix, stir
together cocoa powder, nondairy creamer, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Store in an airtight container until ready to use.

title: spanish rice
directions: Stir together soup, chiles, sour cream, cheese and rice. Bake in 9 x 13 greased pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Melt butter in saucepan; add brown sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture with chips and nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: grandma frances' apple cake
directions: Mix all, except apples, and pat into cookie sheet.
Fill with sliced apples in rows.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar. Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water. Let cool. Add confectioners sugar.

title: dilly bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside. Combine in mixing bowl: cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, baking soda, and egg. Add yeast to mixture. Add flour to form a stiff dough, mixing well after each addition. Cover and let rise in warm place until dough doubles in size (approx. 1 hour). Stir dough down and place in a well greased casserole baking dish. Let rise in warm place until dough doubles in size again. Bake
for 45 minutes at 350° until golden brown. Remove from oven and brush with butter.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine butter, confectioners sugar and flour; blend.
Put into 9 x 13-inch baking pan, spread on bottom.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown.
Beat eggs for filling with sugar, add flour, salt and lemon juice; blend.
Pour onto the hot crust.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Remove from oven.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar and cut into squares.

title: e z yeast rolls
directions: Melt shortening; add sugar, salt and milk.
Heat until mixture is warm.
When slightly cooled, add the egg and flour which has been mixed with the yeast.	Cover and set aside to rise in warm place.
When doubled in size, knead down in bowl and let rise again.
When doubled in size again, turn out onto a floured board and knead again.
Cut into rolls and place on greased baking sheet to rise again.
Bake at 450° about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot with butter.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole dish with butter. Put a layer of cracker crumbs on bottom of dish, then alternate with oysters and crackers until all are used; add spices. Pour oyster juice over top, then add enough milk, 1/2 to 1 cup, making sure crackers on the bottom are moist. Do not mix or stir up. Put a few dabs of butter on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips, in no given order. Pour into 9-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
You need not grease the pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over the top of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mixed veggie casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Mix Cheez Whiz with soup. Microwave until creamy.
Put layer of veggies and cheese in bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle with onion rings.
Put another layer of veggies, cheese mixture and top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° until rings are brown.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix all but chicken and onion soup mix.
Pour into baking pan.
Lay chicken breasts in mixture.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top of chicken.
Cook at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half; remove stem and seeds. Mix meat, Tabasco, garlic salt, pepper, lemon juice, crumbs and half of Jarlsberg cheese together; spoon evenly into pepper halves. Top each half with remaining cheese. Melt butter. Add
garlic salt and brush over the peppers. Sprinkle coarse salt on baking sheet. Place peppers on top of coarse salt and bake in 350° oven about 35 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: new year's eve bean soup
directions: Wash beans and put in a large kettle.
Soak in water overnight.
Add ham or hock. Bring to a boil and simmer 2 to 3 hours. Add vegetables, herbs and spices after cooking 2 hours. Season when beans are tender with lemon juice. Cut up meat and put back in pot.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon into pancake mix.
Stir in apples and add milk, egg and oil.
Bake on a hot, heavy griddle, turning once.
Yields 12 pancakes.

title: italian delight
directions: Saute onion in oleo; brown meat and add salt and pepper, tomato paste, taco sauce and corn.
Simmer; cook noodles and drain.
In large casserole dish, put layer of noodles, layer meat and layer cheese.
Repeat 2 layers.
Bake in moderate (350°) oven a few minutes until cheese bubbles.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over browned pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve hot!

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender; take off bone.
Make biscuit dough; roll out thin.
Cut slices.
Drop dumplings in boiling broth.
Add cream of chicken soup.

title: blue cheese bites
directions: Stir together flour and chives.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add Blue cheese, then blend in enough of the milk to make a soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead gently about 20 times and then shape into 1 inch balls.
Now, combine egg white and water.
Dip balls into egg white mixture; roll in crumbs.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen appetizers.

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar and cinnamon in a bag. Cut biscuits into quarters and drop into bag with sugar mixture. Combine margarine and brown sugar in a saucepan; heat until sugar melts.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Place biscuits in pan.
Pour margarine and sugar mixture over coated biscuits.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes before taking up.

title: marshmallow bars
directions: Butter square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Heat marshmallows and margarine together in 3 quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until marshmallows are melted and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in half of the cereal at a time until evenly coated.
Press in pan; cool.
Cut into about 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: salad (sweet)
directions: Be careful to your selection; do not choose too young and take only such as has been reared in a good moral atmosphere.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, while others keep them in hot water.
This only makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with smiles and flavored with kisses to taste; then wrap them in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of devotion; serve with peaches and cream.
When thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Mix mashed bananas and beaten eggs together.
Stir flour, salt and baking soda into mixtures. Do not overmix.

title: boiled custard
directions: Put milk and cinnamon in top of double boiler.
Heat milk until tiny bubbles appear around edges.
Beat egg yolks slightly with fork.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly to avoid cooked egg specks.
Return to double boiler and cook over hot but not boiling water.
Stir constantly until thick enough to coat a spoon.
Remove cinnamon and add vanilla.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: fresh lemon pie(delicious!)
directions: Bake pie shell.
Heat oven to 325°.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Gradually stir in water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Gradually stir at least half of the hot mixture into egg yolks.
Stir into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil and stir 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir in butter, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: gobs
directions: Cream together sugar, crisco and eggs. Add milk, cocoa (dissolved in boiling water), and vanilla. Add flour, baking soda and baking powder. Drop on greased baking sheet and bake for 5 minutes at 450 degrees.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine onion, potatoes, carrots, celery stalks and water; cook until tender.	Save the liquid.
Stir flour into butter, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk; stir until thickened, then add vegetables and enough liquid to make soup a desired consistency. This will make about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: beef and eggplant bake
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic in skillet until browned; drain. Stir in eggplant, tomatoes, oregano, basil, salt and pepper. Simmer 30 minutes on low heat.
Beat Ricotta, cottage cheese, egg, parsley and 1 tablespoon Parmesan until smooth.
Layer 1/2 of eggplant mixture in 1-quart casserole dish.
Add 1/2 cheese mixture.
Repeat layers and sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add flour and milk, starting with flour and ending with flour.
Grease and lightly dust with flour the tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Put in cold oven.

title: south carolina frogmore stew
directions: Fill large container of a propane cooker halfway with water. Add seasoning; bring to a boil.
Add potatoes; return to a boil and cook 10 minutes.
Add sausage and corn.
Return to a boil; cook 10 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Add shrimp; cook 3 to 5 minutes, or until shrimp turn pink.
Remove with a slotted spoon onto a serving platter or newspaper lined table.
Serve with cocktail sauce.
Makes 12 servings.

title: easy slow cook barbecue
directions: Place all ingredients in large casserole.
Stir.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: deer tenderloin
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Broil tenderloin as needed.
When almost done, wrap in bacon secured with a tooth pick.
Broil, turning often until bacon is done.
Slice between bacon strips.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Combine 1/4 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
In saucepan, heat the fruit, 1 cup sugar and butter until hot.
Pour over batter and bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Serve warm plain or topped with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: scalloped scallops
directions: Combine crackers, salt and butter.
In casserole, arrange alternate layers of crackers and scallops (3 layers of crackers and 2 of scallops).
Pour cream over top; sprinkle with paprika and pepper.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.

title: herbed crackers
directions: Pour oil over crackers and mix.
Combine the salad dressing, lemon pepper, garlic salt and dill weed; sprinkle mixture over crackers.
Stir well.
Let dry thoroughly before serving.

title: white mountain frosting
directions: Put sugar, water and cream of tartar in pan.
Stir until sugar is dissolved and bring to boil.
Add 2 tablespoons syrup to beaten egg whites, beating constantly after adding each spoonful.
Boil syrup until it spins a long thread when dropped from a spoon. Pour gradually on egg whites, beating until mixture forms peaks. Flavor with vanilla or almond.

title: chicken breasts dijon(one of jay's favorites)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, salt and pepper in bowl. Dredge chicken pieces in flour mixture.
Saute chicken in large skillet in 2 tablespoons of butter and the oil, turning once, until golden, about 10 minutes.
Arrange in single layer in a shallow baking dish.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples in a greased baking dish; mix other ingredients and place on top of apples. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Add remaining ingredients with liquid from all cans.
Bring to a boil and simmer 2 hours.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: In a
2-quart
casserole, place 1 cup uncooked rice and cover with
cup
corn.
Empty 1 can tomato sauce over corn; add 1/2 can (3 ounces) water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Next layer, add the
chopped
onion, then the bell pepper and hamburger.
Again, salt
and pepper to taste.	Finally, pour the second can
of tomato sauce over beef.
Add, last, 1/2 can of water (3
ounces). Cover
casserole; bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour. Uncover; bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rice with undiluted soup, green pepper, onion, celery, pimento and chestnuts in bowl.
Pour into pan.
Place chicken breasts on top and dab with butter.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients, including cocoa.
Using low speed mixer add dry ingredients to butter mixture alternating with milk (beginning and ending with dry ingredients).
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour in pan and bake at 325°
for 70 to 90 minutes.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets.
Peel and shred coarsely.
Put butter and cheese in pan over low heat until melted.
Blend sour cream and seasonings.
Fold in potatoes and parsley.
Place in casserole.
Dot with butter and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with Sociables crackers.

title: deep chocolate mint cookies
directions: Over hot (not boiling) water, melt 3/4 cup mint chocolate morsels.
Stir until smooth.
In small bowl combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, syrup, flour, shortening, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour in a partly baked crust and bake in moderate oven (325°) for about 45 minutes.
The nuts float to the top, forming a firm crust that will brown nicely if baked slowly.

title: butter barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter; add onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Use warm.

title: beautiful layered salad
directions: Place lettuce over bottom of pan or bowl.
Add onion, celery, green pepper, carrots and frozen peas, one layer at a time.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread over entire top of salad.
Next, add cheese as a layer, then bacon bits.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill in refrigerator at least 6 hours before serving.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, salt and
baking soda.
Add 1/2 of the flour and 1/2 of sour cream to
butter
and
sugar
mixture.
Blend well.
Add remaining flour
mixture and then remaining sour cream.
Pour into two greased
and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: baba's christmas cookies(rohalyky)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; add flour.
Divide dough into golf size balls.
Refrigerate dough overnight.
Roll out in powdered sugar about 1/4-inch thick; cut into triangular shape pieces.
Fill with preserves; roll up cookies.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden.
Cool; sprinkle with additional powdered sugar.

title: jello salad
directions: Make jello as directed.
Add cheese, mayonnaise and fruits that have been mixed together.
Fold in whipped cream and marshmallows.
Add chopped pecans, if desired.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine Mandarin oranges (well drained), cottage cheese, pineapple, Jell-O, sugar and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with crushed nuts.
Put in fridge.
Keep cold.
Quick, easy and very good.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, sugar, eggs and sour cream.
Pour into sheet pan.
Mix brown sugar, raisins, cinnamon and nuts.
Swirl with knife into cake.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: grouper hawaiian
directions: Sprinkle steaks with 1 teaspoon salt.
Combine next 6 ingredients.
Place one steak in a well-greased baking pan, 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch.
Place rice mixture on the steak and cover with the other steak.
Fasten together with toothpicks or skewers.
Brush top with butter and lay slices of bacon on top.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 40 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add sauce, onion and sugar.
Place crescent rolls into each muffin cup.
Form with fingers to fit muffin cups.
Top with cheese. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: taco pizza snack
directions: Bake prepared pizza crust.
Let cool.
Spread on 1 package of cream cheese.
Pour salsa evenly over cream cheese.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Add whatever toppings you like.
Cut into small squares.
Eat as a finger food.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add cocoa, salt, vanilla and coloring.
Add baking powder to flour and put 1/2 of flour mixture into batter.
Add 1/2 cup of milk.
Beat with mixer.
Add other half of flour and milk. Mix well.
Bake in large tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Mix all together; float an ice ring.
Use pineapple chunks, cherries, etc., inside ring.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together and cook in 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Make icing and pour over cake while still warm.

title: broccoli quiche casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave according to package directions. Dice green pepper and onion.
Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned, approximately 30 minutes.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Saute onion in margarine until transparent.
Add water and broccoli; simmer until broccoli is tender.
Add salmon, chicken bouillon, evaporated milk and flour (which has been mixed together).
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Heat until mixture thickens slightly.

title: cheese cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Cream together Ricotta and cream cheese; add sugar, flour and cornstarch; beat well.
Add vanilla and butter and add beaten eggs and sour cream. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Turn off oven and leave in oven for 3 more hours.
Do not open oven door.
Cool, then refrigerate.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch pan.
In a large bowl mix baking mix, sugar, pumpkin, eggs, oil, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Stir until moistened.
Stir in raisins.
Pour into pan. Bake 45 to 55 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove pan to wire rack for 15 minutes.
Remove bread from pan to cool. Store at room temperature or refrigerate.
Keep wrapped in plastic.

title: wet back
directions: Brown meat with onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 40 minutes.
Serve on Fritos or Doritos.
Top with tomatoes, lettuce, cheese and sauce.

title: kahlua
directions: Dissolve coffee in boiling water.
Add sugar.
Cool and stir well.
Add rum or vodka and vanilla bean.
Put in dark jar and let stand for 30 days in cool place.
Do not refrigerate.
Fill rest of jar with vodka.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar, flour and salt; add egg yolks alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Beat in cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff; beat in remaining sugar.
Spread over pie filling.
Bake at 350° to 375° until light brown.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: christmas cherry cookies
directions: Cream margarine and powdered sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add flour, pecans and vanilla; mix until well blended. Shape dough into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheets. Press cherry in center of cookie.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: quick and easy peanut butter cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Scoop level tablespoonfuls and roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 18 minutes. Remove to a wire rack to cool.
Yields 2 dozen cookies.

title: sweet and sour smokies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except meat and pineapple in fondue pot; mix well. Bring to a boil. Add meat and pineapple; reduce temperature.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, onion flakes and lemon juice.
Spread on serving tray.
Pour cocktail sauce over spread.
Flake crab meat or mini shrimp.
Garnish with parsley flakes.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and salt; boil to soft-ball stage. Add peanut butter and vanilla. Cool without stirring to room temperature. Beat until mixture is creamy. Pour into well-buttered pan. Cut in squares.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Cook noodles until done and drain.
Brown hamburger and onion. Mix noodles, sauerkraut, hamburger and soup together.
Place in baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Salt and pepper to taste or use Morton's Nature's Seasoning for flavor.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix the sugar, flour and cornstarch.
Stir in milk gradually. Cook over medium heat in double boiler, stirring constantly, until the mixture thickens and boils.
Boil for 1 minute.
Slowly stir half the mixture into egg yolks.
Then blend into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute more until thickened, stirring constantly.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Boil water; add noodles and 1 teaspoon of salt.
Cook 15 minutes until tender; drain.
Blend 2 tablespoons of margarine with flour, 1 teaspoon of salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add noodles, cheese, tuna and eggs.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining margarine with cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: hamburger
directions: Cook the beef, dress the bun with mayonnaise, mustard, ketchup, lettuce, pickle and onion, then you have your hamburger.
Then warm the bun and you have a delicious hamburger.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over broccoli and set aside.
Saute onions and celery in butter; add soup and milk and simmer for 3 minutes. Add Cheez Whiz and mix well.
Add broccoli and rice and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 325° to 350° for 40 minutes.

title: ann landers' world famous meat loaf
directions: Beat the first 7 ingredients thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan. Cover with the bacon (if you like that flavor).
Pour over all the tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: jalapeno chicken
directions: Crush Doritos and line bottom of casserole dish.
Chop up chicken in small pieces and lay on Doritos.
Mix soups, milk, pimento and jalapenos; simmer.
Saute onion and bell pepper in small amount of oleo to soften, then add to soup mixture.
Pour over chicken; cover with grated cheese.
Heat at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in medium bowl.
Cream brown sugar, granulated sugar, margarine and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Beat in egg whites.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients alternately with water.
Stir in morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoon onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until centers are set.
Cool for 2 minutes.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Split
wings
at each joint and discard tips.
Wash and pat dry.
Bake on a rack in a roasting pan at 425° for 1 hour, turn halfway
through cooking time.
Line pan with foil first (saves on cleanup).
Do not cover wings when cooking.
Remove from
pan and cool.
In saucepan melt margarine and add other ingredients. When
cool	pour over wings.
To reheat place in 350° oven until just begins to bubble.

title: thick strawberry shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender. Blend at high speed until smooth,
about
1	minute.
Serve	immediately.
Makes approximately one 12 ounce serving.
Calories per serving: 79.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Cook the first 7 ingredients together until raisins are soft. Allow to cool; add the next 5 ingredients and mix well by hand. Batter will be very stiff.
Grease and flour Bundt or 2 loaf pans. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Use a 1 1/2-quart casserole and put the sugar and cornstarch in first.
Mix, then add eggs.
Next the corn and milk.
Dot with butter and bake on 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: el dorado casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic powder in oil.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Mix sour cream, cottage cheese and chilies.
Line a greased casserole dish (9 x 13-inch) with chips. Add in layers of 1/2 meat mixture, 1/2 the cream mixture and 1/2 of cheese.
Repeat layers of meat, sour cream and Monterey cheese. I reserve some crushed chips to sprinkle over top.
This gives a crunchy top.
Some prefer the plain, cheesy top.
Bon appetit.

title: three-c bread
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, mace and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Combine eggs, oil and milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in carrots, coconut and cherries. Pour into three 21 ounce pie filling cans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours (or pour batter into one greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes).
Cool in cans 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Wrap and store overnight before slicing.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine
potatoes,
sugar,
cinnamon and salt.
Stir in eggs, milk
and margarine.
Bake at 400° until knife put into center comes out clean for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy chili con carne
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: eunice tutterback's torte
directions: Slice the pound cake into 5 or 7 slices.
Melt chocolate chips and stir into the sour cream.
Add the butter.
Fill and cover top and sides of the cake with the chocolate mixture.
Do not cover ends.
Refrigerate.
Serves 6 to 8.
Can be frozen.

title: spaghetti
directions: Mix the ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Cook for 15 minutes, then add the tomatoes, paste, sugar, salt and bay leaves. Cook for 1 hour on low heat.

title: malt
directions: Mix the ingredients in blender until very thick.
Yields 1 serving.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Boil together milk and sugar.
Add marshmallows and coconut.
Pour over cake while hot.
Bring to boil 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup cream, butter and almonds, then add chocolate chips.
Pour over cake.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook, drain and cool sausage.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Put mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake next morning at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: grandma's goulash
directions: Put hamburger and onion in fry pan.
Fry just until redness is gone, don't brown.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: frito salad
directions: Wash lettuce, pat dry and tear in bite-size pieces.
Place in large salad bowl.
Dice tomatoes in small pieces and place on lettuce.
Drain beans and spread on tomatoes.
Grate cheese and put on beans.
Crush Fritos and spread on cheese.
(Note:
Make several openings in bag and crush by squeezing bag.)
Just before serving, pour salad dressing evenly on top.
Salad should be served with salad tongs so that each serving contains all layers.

title: cheese straws
directions: Blend grated cheese, butter and soy sauce.
Add the flour and mix well.
Shape into small balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together and roll out.

title: shrimp and spinach stir-fry
directions: Thaw shrimp, if frozen.
Shell and devein shrimp.
Halve shrimp lengthwise.

title: bean fritters
directions: Drain the beans.
Set aside.
Combine egg, milk and beans. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add beans mixture to dry ingredients.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into deep Crisco heated to 365°.
Fry a few at a time, until fritters are golden brown, about 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes about 24.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain and put in cooker.
Brown bacon with onion; drain.
Crumble bacon.
Add both to cooker along with remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours in crock-pot.

title: butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg and press into a floured, greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: working mom's red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Add other ingredients to cake mix.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs real good. Add sugar and beat well. Add hot milk, melted butter, salt and vanilla. Put into a buttered casserole. Set in a pan of hot water; bake in 350° oven until firm or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: banana crepes
directions: Blend ingredients in a blender.
Pour a small circle of mixture into the middle of a greased hot frypan. Tip pan so crepe spreads out very thin.
Cook lightly on both sides.
Serve with fresh berry puree (to which a small amount of apple juice concentrate has been added).
Serve flat like pancake or roll up like crepes.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix and chill overnight.

title: prudence's rhubarb jam
directions: Mix in a pan that one can cook jam in, let stand all night in refrigerator.
In the morning place on low flame & stir well.
When it starts to boil, boil for 15 minutes.
Remove from fire and add 1 box (3 oz.) strawberry or raspberry jello.
Stir well and put in jars or glasses.
Cover with wax.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour over chicken and cook for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
(This is enough sauce for two chickens.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix with oil, sugar and salt.
Mix until smooth. Add zucchini, plain flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and raisins and/or nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased loaf pan.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour which has been sifted with soda and salt; add milk.
Pour into a well-greased and floured pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Sometimes I make it with 1/4 cup catsup and 1/4 cup barbecue sauce.

title: easy venison roll-ups
directions: Remove fat from steaks.
Brown sausage until crumbly; drain off grease.
Add stuffing mix and water.
Mix thoroughly.
Divide into small portions and place in the middle of steaks.
Spread stuffing out on steaks.
Roll steaks.
Place, seam side down, in a baking pan.
Sprinkle pepper and paprika.
Pour soup over roll-ups.
Bake in a covered pan for 30 minutes at 350° or until meat is tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Drain English peas and green beans.
Add pimento and onion. Mix all other ingredients and add to mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Drain and serve.

title: spring lemon pie
directions: Blend frozen whipped topping
with lemonade.
Stir in condensed milk.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Decorate top with lemon slices and chill 3 hours before serving.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut the tops off 4 of the tomatoes and trim a thin slice off the bottom so they will sit up easily.
Hollow out the tomatoes with a spoon.
Discarding the insides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dice remaining tomato, squash, red onion, cucumber and zucchini.
Combining in a bowl with lemon juice, cilantro or parsley and olive oil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Fill empty tomatoes with vegetable mixture.
Use any remaining filling as a wonderful side salad to any meal.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions. Put broccoli and the rest of the ingredients into crock-pot. Cook on low. Serves 8.

title: old-fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in rice, raisins, lemon rind and juice.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart baking dish.
Combine bread crumb and butter; sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a 1 1/2-quart or 2-quart casserole and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Top with butter and bread crumbs. Bake additional 5 minutes.

title: quick praline strips
directions: Arrange graham crackers in an ungreased 9 x 13 x 1-inch pan. Place margarine and sugar in a saucepan.
Heat to boiling and boil one minute.
Remove from heat and stir in pecans.
Spoon and spread
over crackers.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Cut each cracker in half and remove to racks while warm.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out 1 loaf bread dough to fit greased 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet.
Add remaining ingredients layering on top of dough in order given.
Sprinkle lightly with oregano over last layer of cheese.
Roll out second loaf of bread dough to fit top.
Pinch edges to seal.
Brush top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour until golden brown.

title: texas biscuits
directions: Add yeast, buttermilk and oil to warm water in bowl.
Then mix 1 cup flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add to the yeast mixture.
Then add 5 more cups flour (one at a time).
Knead well. Place dough in fridge in covered bowl and use as needed.
Dough will keep in fridge for weeks.
No need to let dough rise before using; the dough rises in oven.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cream cheese salsa spread
directions: Place cream cheese on rimmed plate.
Let stand at room temperature about 30 minutes to soften.
Pour Pace sauce over and around cream cheese.
Garnish with cilantro if desired.
Serve with vegetable dippers, crackers or chips.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix the drained fruits together and then add condensed sweetened milk and then Cool
Whip.
Pour into a cooled graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: stir-fry
directions: Brown rice in 2 tablespoons oil.
Cook rice in 1 cup water after browning.
Cook chicken.
In 2 tablespoons oil saute sliced onion, sliced pepper, diced celery and sliced carrot.
Remove chicken from bone and add to vegetables.
Stir in rice.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, water and sugar; cook until it becomes clear, then add jello.
Let cool; add fresh strawberries and put in graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: red snapper florentine
directions: Squeeze spinach to remove as much liquid as possible.
In ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish, mix spinach with mayonnaise, sour cream and 1/2 the Parmesan.
Spread in pan evenly.
Rinse fish; pat dry and arrange in single layer on top of spinach, overlapping thinner edge of fillets, if necessary.
(Can be made ahead up to this point.
Cover and refrigerate for up to 6 hours.)

title: biscuits
directions: Place yeast in a cup.
Add warm water.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar.
Cut in fat and add the buttermilk or sour milk to the flour and fat mixture.
Stir yeast and water to get the lumps out.
Add flour mixture.
Stir until you have a dough.
Add more flour, if necessary.

title: angel rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and cut in shortening or butter until crumbly.
In a separate bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Add yeast and buttermilk to the dry ingredients and mix lightly but thoroughly.
Cover tightly with plastic; the dough will keep in the refrigerator for a week.
Punch it down occasionally.
When you are ready to bake, preheat oven to 400°.
Roll out dough on a floured board to about 1/8-inch thickness and cut into 2-inch squares or use a cutter to make rounds.
Brush the top with melted butter if desired.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Shape into 12 balls.
Brown in oil; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs. Simmer for 15 minutes, turning frequently until meatballs are well glazed.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crunch topping
directions: Knead well.
Sprinkle over the top of pies, cobblers or cakes, then bake.

title: swapples
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Peel and cut sweet potatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Saute apples and sweet potatoes in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt. Add chopped pecans.
Put remaining melted butter and maple syrup over it.
Bake at 350° for about an hour or until potatoes are soft.
Serves 16.

title: spritz
directions: Stir together the flour and baking powder.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine until softened.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg, vanilla and almond extract; beat well. Gradually add flour mixture; beat until well mixed.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder and salt and add to brown sugar, granulated sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla. Add remaining ingredients.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 minutes for crisp cookies or 12 minutes for chewy cookies.

title: french-style bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, 1/2 can onions and soup until moistened.
Bake, uncovered, in a greased casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°. Top with 1/2 can onions and bake for 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: luscious baked chocolate cheesecake(yields one 9-inch cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
For filling, in a large mixing bowl beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add condensed milk and beat until smooth.
Add chocolate, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Bake for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill until serving.

title: buttered carrots
directions: Wash carrots.
Scrape and cut in 1/4-inch pieces diagonally. Place garlic salt and water in microwave-safe dish.
Stir to dissolve.
Add carrots.
Cover and microwave on High for 4 minutes. Stir well.
Add cut up margarine on top of carrots.
Cover and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Serves 4.

title: squash casserole
directions: Add cheese if desired. Save a little butter and stuffing to sprinkle on top. Boil squash and onions until tender. Mix everything in a large bowl. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, eggs and butter.
Stir well.
Sift together baking powder and vanilla.
Add flour to batter.
Stir until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mexican vegetable soup
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning mix, juice, beans, vegetables and tomato paste.
Mix well.
Bring just to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Top each serving with crushed corn chips and Cheddar cheese.

title: pistachio ice cream cake
directions: Mix and spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; chill 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad 1
directions: Peel and seed orange.
Seed and core apples.
Chop cranberries, apples and oranges.
Mix with partially drained pineapple.
Dissolve the jello in the boiling water.
Add sugar. Mix all ingredients with nuts.
Pour into mold and chill until set.
Serve with any fowl.

title: upside-down onion cornbread
directions: Peel onion; cut 6 very thin slices from center of onion. Finely chop remaining onion; set aside.
Melt butter in a 9-inch ovenproof skillet over medium heat.
Arrange onion slices over bottom. Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until onion is partially cooked.

title: hacienda chicken
directions: Melt oleo in heavy skillet or kettle.
Add onion; cook until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes, water, green pepper, mushrooms and liquid, clove, parsley, paprika, salt and pepper.
Cut chicken in serving pieces; add to ingredients in kettle.
Cover; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Add rice and olives; continue cooking until rice is done and chicken is tender (2 fryers are nice to use).

title: louisiana pralines
directions: Boil all ingredients in a medium-sized saucepan to a soft ball stage.
Take off heat and cool 10 minutes.
Then beat until thick enough to drop spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Punch must be made 1 day in advance.
In a 6-quart container, mix together first 7 ingredients.
Loosely cover and freeze until firm.
Remove punch from freezer about 4 hours before serving, partially thaw.
To serve, break into chunks.
Add ginger ale and stir until slushy.
Yield:
26 servings.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Cut up celery and onion.
Combine all ingredients, except tomato juice and mix well.
Form into balls.
Put the tomato juice into pressure cooker.
Put meat balls in pressure cooker and cook 15 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Place chopped chicken, chilies and onion into 2-quart saucepan.
In large skillet, combine 2 cups broth and chicken soup.
Blend and heat until smooth.
Put 1 cup broth mixture into chicken, onion, chili mixture or enough to moisten it.
Dip tortillas into skillet and fill each with 1 spoonful of chicken. Roll and place into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spoon remainder of soup mixture onto enchiladas and top with grated cheese.
Place in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugars and syrup to a boil.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour over Special K.
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet or wax paper.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and cut into bite size pieces.
Arrange 1 layer of tortillas; top with a layer each of chicken, cheese, onions and bell peppers.
Arrange another layer, starting again with a layer of tortillas and repeat the layers.
Top with remaining tortillas.
Mix all the soups and tomatoes together. Pour over the layered ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Cook in unbaked pie shell for 30 to 35 minutes at 340°.

title: beer roast
directions: Place beef in roasting pan and top with ingredients.
Bake as follows:
at 250° to 275° for 4 to 6 hours or 225° for 8 hours. Slice meat and serve with juice.
Can be used as barbecue on buns. Serves 15.

title: chicken log
directions: Mix and roll in pecans.
Chill and serve on crackers.

title: peppermint pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk; beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla; beat.
Pour 1/3 of batter and crushed candy in separate bowl; stir well.
Pour 1/2 of remaining batter into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Add peppermint batter, then add remaining batter on top of peppermint batter.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, or as your oven cooks. Turn out onto wire rack to cool.
A chocolate frosting on cake goes great with taste of peppermint.

title: three bean salad
directions: Toss and refrigerate for 3 hours.
A drop or two of Worcestershire sauce if desired.

title: corn meal with okra
directions: Fry together salt bacon and okra.
Add water to corn meal, okra and bacon.
Cook like you would cook grits.
Serve with pork, meat or fish.

title: port wine cranberry jelly
directions: Blend cranberry juice and sugar over low heat. Bring to a rapid full boil. Boil 1 minute. Add Certo liquid. Again bring to boil and boil 1 minute. Add wine and again bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.

title: chicken how-so
directions: Cut chicken into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
In medium skillet over medium heat, brown chicken in margarine until golden.
Combine mushroom soup, water, bouillon cube, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, curry powder and poppy seed.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken. Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add bamboo shoots, celery, onion and mushrooms. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Stir in green pepper and white wine. Cover and simmer 2 to 3 minutes. Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip according to directions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Garnish with red and green cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: microwave peanutty chocolate pie
directions: In large microwavable bowl, combine sugar and cornstarch. Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Microwave on High (100%), stirring 3 times with a fork or wire whisk, 7 to 9 minutes or until mixture boils.
Boil 1 minute, stir in peanut butter.

title: fudge candy
directions: Mix all together well; cook until it comes to hard boil, let boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Take off and beat until it becomes fluffy. Add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let cool; cut into small square pieces.

title: wild rice casserole(crock-pot)
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot; stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low setting for 6 to 10 hours (high setting for 2 to 3 1/2 hours).
Makes 6 to 8 servings (2 1/2 quarts).

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and put in casserole dish. Can be put in 9 x 13 pan.

title: old fashioned fruit salad
directions: Beat egg.
Mix flour and sugar, then add to egg along with lemon juice and juice from small can of pineapple.
Mix well. Cook over low heat until smooth and thick.
Set aside to cool completely.
Wash, drain and chop fruit.
Beat whipped cream until stiff; add to cooled dressing.
Pour over fruit and mix well. Refrigerate.
Can add pecans, if desired.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and beat again.
Beat in margarine and vanilla.
Add flour and beat well.
Add pecans. Spray cooking spray in loaf pan just before pouring in mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese scalloped carrots
directions: Prepare carrots and slice.
Heat carrots, water and salt. Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk gradually, stirring until thick.
Alternate layers in 1 1/2-quart casserole of carrots and cheese, ending with carrots.
Pour sauce over and top with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick and easy baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place ingredients in a 3-quart casserole dish in the order listed.
Toss lightly to mix well. Bake, uncovered, for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: corn dog mix
directions: Mix and dip hot dogs on a stick with mixture.
Cook in hot deep grease until golden brown.

title: squash supreme
directions: Combine squash, pimento, onion, carrots, sour cream and undiluted soup.
In separate bowl, toss together stuffing mix and melted margarine.
Mix half of stuffing with squash mixture.
Spread in 3 quart shallow pan.
Top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pepper chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and Italian seasoning. Heat 3 tablespoons oil in large skillet and saute chicken over medium heat about 5 to 10 minutes or until golden brown and cooked through.
Remove chicken from skillet and keep warm.

title: golden apple bundles
directions: In a bowl combine the apples, walnuts, brown sugar, raisins, flour, lemon peel and cinnamon; set aside.
Roll pastry to 1/8 inch thickness. Cut into 5 inch circles.
Spoon about 1/4 cup apple mixture into center of each circle.
Moisten edges of pastry with water.
Fold over and seal edges with a fork.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400°; bake 10 minutes longer.
Brush each with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl (including the reserved cherry juice).
Line graham cracker box with overlapping waxed paper.
Pack mixture lightly into box.
Cover with waxed paper and refrigerate for 24 hours before slicing.

title: cheese straws
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Thoroughly blend cheese and margarine. Stir in Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Add flour; mix well.
Roll dough between two sheets of waxed paper to 1/8-inch thickness. Cut into 3 x 1-inch strips.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: perfect meringue topper for pies
directions: Beat at high speed, adding sugar until peaks are stiff.
Place under broiler on lower rack until nice and brown.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir cranberry sauce and pineapple with juice together.
Process in food processor for one second.
Add cranberry mixture to gelatin and put in a greased glass dish.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares.
Unmold on lettuce leaves or ivy. Top with mayonnaise.

title: almond chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, grapes, celery, onions and eggs.
In another bowl, combine the next nine ingredients; stir until smooth.
Pour over the chicken mixture and toss gently. Stir in almonds and serve immediately or refrigerate and add the almonds just before serving.

title: crabmeat melts
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Top each cracker with 1 tablespoon of the crabmeat mixture.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: sandy's breakfast casserole
directions: Personal choice of Owens sausage and type of grated cheese.

title: corn pudding
directions: In separate bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, flour, sugar and salt. Pour mixture into greased casserole dish.
Add corn.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow Solomon's description for making a good boy in Proverbs 23:14 and you will have a good cake.

title: cantaloupe pickles
directions: Remove rind and seeds, cut in 1-inch pieces.
Bring vinegar and water to a rolling boil.
Break cinnamon.
Put spices in bag and add to solution.
Pour over chunks.
Stand all night in refrigerator.
Next day, drain chunks and bring to a rolling boil. Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add chunks and boil gently until clear, 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove spices.
Pack into jars 1/2 inch from top, add boiling syrup to 1/2 inch of top.
Seal while hot.
Yields 3 1/2 pints.

title: eskimo cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except powdered sugar.
Roll into tablespoon size balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours and eat.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Bone and cut chicken in about 2-inch pieces.
Place chicken in bottom of large casserole dish.
Top with egg slices.
Add mixed vegetables.
Mix soups together.
Spoon on top of vegetables.
Mix flour, milk and mayonnaise until well blended.
Spoon on top of vegetables and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crust is lightly browned.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and almonds. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with cheese and almonds. Keep, covered, overnight in the refrigerator. Take out 1 hour before baking. Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 35 minutes. Makes 9 to 12 servings. Great salad for showers.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Heat tomato juice.
Dissolve jello in hot juice.
Add lemon juice, salt, paprika, pepper, cloves and onion juice.
Pour into ring mold or 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake by package direction.
Put Pet milk, sugar and margarine in pan, heat to melt sugar, but don't boil.
Add coconut flavoring.
Pour over baked cake while still hot.
Punch holes in cake with fork so it will soak up milk and sugar mixture.
Mix coconut into sour cream frosting and ice cake.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend with other ingredients 2 or 3 minutes, until light.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix 3/4 cup half and half with the dozen eggs; stir until smooth.
Set aside.
Mix 2/3 cup half and half with the can of soup; set aside.
Fry bacon and cool; drain.
Scramble egg mixture until light and fluffy.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Crumble bacon on top.
Layer mushrooms.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Pour soup mixture over all and place the Tater Tots on top.
Can refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or 45 to 50 minutes if taken out of the refrigerator.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach.
Completely drain all water.
Mix all ingredients together and form into balls.
Cook for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion.
Drain and add all beans and other ingredients.
Cook at 350° in oven for 1 hour.
Cook in crock-pot on low 5 to 6 hours.

title: mrs. lee's butterscotch-pecan cookies(this is a refrigerated cookie)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add nuts.
Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Make into three rolls; wrap in wax paper.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Cut 1/8-inch thick.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown, according to thickness.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put berries in 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Blend remaining ingredients and sprinkle on berries.
Bake 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: miniature cheesecake
directions: Prepare Crust:
Combine graham crackers with melted butter and dash of cinnamon.
Press into an 8 x 11-inch pan or muffin tins.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white with water until frothy. Add pecans and coat well.
Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon in medium sized bowl. Add nuts and mix well until well coated.
Bake on buttered cookie sheet in 225° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool, store tightly covered.
Good Snacking.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar, cut in oleo until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press mixture on bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Blend Egg Beaters, lemon juice, lemon peel and remaining flour and sugar.
Pour over crust.
Bake 15 minutes or more, until set.
Cool slightly, sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Cool.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.

title: rolled stuffed lasagna
directions: *Low-fat alternative:
Substitute 8 ounces cottage cheese for Ricotta.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut carrots, onions, celery and potatoes into bite size pieces. Grease large flat casserole.
Place raw beef on the bottom.
Layer vegetables on top.
sprinkle water, salt, pepper, sugar and tapioca over top of vegetables.
Pour tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes and vine on top.
Cover with foil and bake 6 hours at 275 degrees.
Can prepare the night before and kept in refrigerator until its time to bake.

title: nacho taco salad
directions: In large skillet, brown onion and meat.
Drain.
Add seasoning mix and 3/4 cup water.
Then add kidney beans, salt and pepper. Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes; drain, peel and mash.
In a saucepan, warm milk and margarine until margarine is melted; remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, egg, cinnamon, nutmeg and pecans.
Mix with sweet potatoes.
Place in casserole and heat in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Crush Oreos.
Place 1/2 in the bottom of 11 x 17-inch pan. Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
In bowl, combine pudding, milk and vanilla.
Beat mixture until the consistency of pudding.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes, drain and mash.
(Use 2 cans sweet potatoes, drained, if you buy cans.)
Add sugar, eggs, butter and Pet milk.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper until smooth. Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well. Cover. Chill. Makes 5 cups. Great with grilled hamburgers.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Mix cake according to the box with the exception of using lemon pudding instead of vanilla.
Grease mini muffin pan and fill 1/3 full with batter.
Dip cakes in topping while hot.
Set on wax paper to cool.
Makes 95 to 110 cookies.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve 2 boxes of Jell-O in 4 cups hot water and stir in sugar,
then add cold water and orange juice and pineapple juice. Pour in a punch bowl, then add ginger ale or Sprite.

title: linda's refrigerator pickles
directions: Place pickles, onion and green pepper in pan and cover with ice cubes.
Let set for 2 hours.

title: pretzels
directions: Form dough in desired width and style pretzel in shape.
Place in greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° about 1 hour.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs with fork; add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Stir until mixed well; bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 55 minutes. Place baking dish in pan containing hot water.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg, if desired.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix margarine, confectioners sugar, flour and salt and pat in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade pork sausage
directions: Mix ground pork and all spices thoroughly.
Shape into patties and freeze.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Gradually add eggs, one at a time. Slowly add other ingredients, the vanilla last. Roll thin, but do not use any more flour than called for, if possible.
Bake in moderately slow oven. Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake about 12 to 13 minutes or done at 400°.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook the cup of grits according to directions on package.
Add butter, Worcestershire, cheese, garlic and Tabasco.
Let cool. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into cooled grits and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes until slightly brown on top.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cream margarine and eggs with a fork.
Add stuffing mix, cheese and spinach.
Roll into balls.
Freeze for 10 to 15 minutes on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Cut the potatoes up.
Make hard potatoes with them.
Put them in a pan.
Bake them for 15 minutes.
Put them on a plate.
Mash them with the masher.
Turn on the mixer; mix them with it.
Put them on the plate.
Then you eat them.

title: onion casserole
directions: Cook onions 15 to 20 minutes.
Place half in baking dish. Sprinkle with half cracker crumbs, then add half Parmesan cheese. Repeat layer of onions, crumbs and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 3-inch pan.
(Must be a deep pan.) Cover bottom with coconut, then layer of nuts.
Prepare cake mix per directions.
Pour over coconut-nut layers.
Combine oleo, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Spoon over cake.
Do not stir!!!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken wild rice casserole
directions: Saute pepper, mushrooms and onion.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart uncovered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Make 2 or 3 rolls out of your dough and roll real thin. Spread sausage lightly over dough.
Roll up, wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight.
Slice and brown at 350° until brown.

title: spanish rice with beef
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and green pepper together until meat is browned.
Drain in a colander; pat dry with a paper towel. Wipe pan drippings from pan with a paper towel.

title: fast fudge
directions: Mix sugar and water in saucepan; boil rapidly for exactly 1 minute.
Pour over peanut butter and vanilla in bowl; beat until thick.
Pour into buttered pan and cut into squares when cool.
To make chocolate fudge, add 3 tablespoons cocoa to sugar.

title: cream of peanut soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add flour and peanut butter.
Stir until peanut butter is melted.
Gradually add broth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in heavy cream; heat a few minutes longer, until hot.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine sour cream and cream of chicken soup in small bowl. Cook carrots and onion in 4 tablespoons butter until tender. Remove from heat.

title: easy oven chuck roast
directions: Mix together steak sauce, soup mix and mushroom soup.
Brush over chuck roast.
Wrap in heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Sift flour over fruit and mix with creamed butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: hot weather cookies
directions: Mix together sugar and butter; add cocoa and milk.
Stir until comes to a boil in a saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Keep refrigerated in the summer.

title: chicken gary(serves 8)
directions: Pound chicken breasts until thin.
Dredge with flour that has been seasoned with salt and pepper.
Dip in melted butter and lay side by side in large baking pan.
Do not overlap!
Arrange sauteed mushrooms decoratively over each breast.
Sprinkle with cheese; pour over cream and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
This is an easy dish for last minute entertaining that always works.
Serve with rice pilaf and fresh green vegetable.

title: old-fashioned boiled dressing
directions: Mix sugar, salt, flour and mustard.
Beat egg slightly.
Add dry ingredients, water and vinegar.
Mix to a smooth paste. Cook over low heat and blend in butter.
Makes 1 cup.

title: pineapple honey glaze
directions: Cook until thick.
Forty-five minutes before ham is done, spread glaze over it.

title: tropical cherry pie
directions: Cook cherries, pineapple, cornstarch, sugar and salt until thick.
Add food coloring and jello while hot and stir until dissolved.
Add bananas and nuts.
Cool.
After cooled, place in pie shells.

title: herb rice
directions: Saute rice and onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Cover and cook slowly for 30 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: texas cornbread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,	adding	meal
and baking powder last. Pour
into a greased long casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for approximately
minutes	or longer.
When baked, pour 1 stick of melted butter over cornbread and serve warm.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix Wesson oil and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease large baking sheet.
Combine sugar and corn syrup in a microwave-safe bowl.
Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Cook on High 4 more minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook on High for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add baking soda stir until light and foamy.
Pour into the greased baking sheet.
Cool. Break into pieces.
Yields 1 pound.

title: easy breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Tear bread into medium size pieces and put into dish.
Sprinkle browned sausage over bread.
In a bowl combine beaten eggs, cheese, salt and pepper; pour over sausage.
Put in refrigerator overnight. Bake the next morning at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 c. cheese, sour cream, pepper and pimento, 1/2 can of onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with rest of cheese and onions.

title: grandmom's gingersnaps
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Sift flour mixture over creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Form into small balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in an 8 cup bowl.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Serve with cut vegetables.
Makes 8 cups.

title: carrot and zucchini saute
directions: Slice the carrots and zucchini about 1/4 inch thick.
Melt the butter in a frying pan over medium heat; stir in carrots and cook 2 minutes, then stir in the zucchini, garlic, rosemary, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir until zucchini is heated through, then add 1 or 2 teaspoon water and cover pan.
Cook over medium heat until carrots are barely fork tender, shaking pan and stirring occasionally.
Don't overcook; a little crunch won't hurt.
Stir in capers, if used, and serve.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cool.
Make pudding as directed on box.
Break cake into pieces and layer in punch bowl as follows:
1/2 cake, 1/2 pudding, 1 can pineapple, 1 can pie filling, 1/2 Cool Whip and nuts.
Repeat each layer once more. Keep refrigerated.

title: texas pecan candy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Grease and flour tube pan with removable sides.
Combine dried fruit with flour; toss to coat well.
Add pecans and coconut.
Add milk and stir to mix well. Spoon evenly in pan, smoothing the top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 250°. Cool in pan on rack.
When cool, wrap tightly in foil. Refrigerate for at least 2 weeks.
Cake cuts best when cold. Slice thin.

title: champagne punch
directions: Bring frozen concentrates to room temperature.
Prechill all other ingredients.
Pour into punch bowl over large ice ring.
Add 7-Up and champagne last.
Float orange slices in punch.

title: dutch bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight and drain.
Add water to cover and cook. Add seasoning and meat.
Cook until beans separate.
Add soup and cook another 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Place first 10 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cook over boiling water until thick, stirring several times.
When thick, add soaked gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Let cool completely, stirring once or twice.

title: hamburger mixture for spaghetti
directions: Cook hamburger meat with the onions and garlic.
In a separate large pan, add the tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, green pepper, cinnamon, salt, oregano, chili powder and the mushrooms.
Add meat mixture.
Bring to boil, then turn heat down and simmer a long time, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Add small amount of sugar.
Pour this over cooked spaghetti.
Serve with garlic bread toast and salad.

title: millie's potato soup
directions: Add potatoes, pimento, salt and pepper to white sauce and heat thoroughly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: Take some of the salt out of the cod fish; boil several times, changing the water each time or leave it for 6 hours in tap water, changing the water every 2 hours.

title: dilled rice
directions: Melt butter or margarine. Add dill weed, salt and bouillon granules. Cook and stir until blended. Cook white rice. Cook wild rice. Add to butter mixture. Stir in commercial sour cream until the right consistency for a side dish to chicken, ham or meat of your preference. Serves 4.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: In a large bowl combine the rolled oats, flour, whet germ, dry milk, soda, salt and brown sugar.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and butter.
Add all at once to dry ingredients and stir until well blended.
Preheat griddle.
Grease or oil lightly.
Pour about 3 tablespoons of batter for each pancake.
Spread to about 3-inches. Cook until top is bubbly and appears dry.
Turn and cook other side until browned.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Line the pie crust with strawberries, reserving about 1 cup of berries for the glaze. Simmer 1 cup strawberries and the water for 3-4 minutes. Combine cornstarch and sugar, add to the cooked berries along with the lemon juice. Cook until this mixture is thick and clear. Pour over the strawberries in the pie crust and chill. Top with fresh cream or whipped topping. A great taste of Summer!

title: baked seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the potato chips.
Put into baking dish.
Spread the chips over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
In a large skillet, slowly brown chicken on both sides in vegetable oil.
Pour reserved sauce mixture over chicken.
Simmer, uncovered for 8 to 10 minutes or until chicken is cooked and sauce is thickened a bit.
Turn and baste occasionally.	4 to 6 servings.

title: tomato pie
directions: Spray casserole with Pam.
Layer tomatoes, bell pepper, salt and pepper with generous sprinkles of sugar (maybe 1 tablespoon, heaping).
Make as many layers as pan will hold.
Cut cheese into Bisquick.
Add enough milk to make a soupy batter.
Pour over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; reduce to 300° for 20 minutes.

title: microwave bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir well.
Microwave another 4 minutes; stir well. Microwave another 4 minutes.
Cool and put in container and refrigerate.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
(You may add more vegetables if you wish.)
Drain well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Mix onions, mayonnaise and cheese together and spread over vegetables.
Melt margarine.
Mix with cracker crumbs and sprinkle over top. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Drain and flake chicken.
Mix with soup, milk and thawed and drained vegetables, broccoli and rice.
Add 1/2 package Cheddar cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Spray 8 1/2 x 11-inch Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions for 5 minutes more.

title: swedish veal in wine sauce
directions: Lightly flour veal and pound thin.
Cut in strips.
In large skillet, saute strips in butter, until all are lightly browned on both sides, using more butter if needed.
Remove from pan and place in shallow casserole.
Saute onion in skillet until clear. Add flour; mix well.
Add chicken broth, wine and seasonings. Stir until thickened.
Pour over veal.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or maybe a little longer.
Serve with wild rice.

title: spicy tortilla soup
directions: Boil chopped onion, garlic and broth.
Add tomatoes, chilies, cilantro and cumin.
Stir, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add water, salt, pepper, sugar, lime juice and chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Add cheese and chips when ready to eat.
Put cheese and chips in a bowl and fill with soup.
Put cilantro on top.

title: creamy chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender and set aside.
In a large 4-quart pot, place soups and add 1 cup hot chicken bouillon; mix well over medium heat.
Add diced potatoes, peas and carrots. Cut chicken into small pieces.
Add to mixture.
Add pepper to taste.
Simmer for 5 to 8 minutes.
May be served over hot biscuits or rice.
If too thick, add more liquid.
Enjoy!

title: barbecue chicken for the grill
directions: Place chicken in a shallow glass dish. In a small saucepan, combine vinegar, butter, salt, pepper, water and spices. Bring to a gentle boil. Pour over quartered chicken. Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours, turning once.

title: peanut butter frosts
directions: Combine flour, oats, sugar and soda; add butter, peanut butter and egg.
Stir until well blended.
Mixture will be crumbly. Press into a greased cookie sheet (large).
Bake at 350°
for 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugars, beating at medium speed, until light and fluffy.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Stir in buttermilk.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In a bowl, mix first 5 ingredients.
In pressure cooker, mix tomato soup and water.
Make meat mixture into walnut size meatballs.
Put into the tomato soup mixture.
Put lid on pressure cooker; set control at 10 pound pressure.
Cook for 10 minutes after starts to jiggle.

title: carrot-pineapple salad
directions: Prepare jello.
Refrigerate until soft set.
Add pineapple and carrots.
Return to refrigerator until set.
Enjoy.

title: chicken rice salad
directions: Prepare rice according to directions. Stir in remaining ingredients. Serve warm or chilled.

title: angel almonds
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Ball dough.
Form into crescents and set on ungreased cookie sheet with room between.
Bake in a 375° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Watch; they should be a pink, rather than golden.
Yields 120 dainty ones.

title: stand-by salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables and pimientos well.
Mix all vegetables together.
Toss gently.
In a saucepan, combine oil, sugar, vinegar, water, lemon juice and paprika.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; allow to cook 5 minutes.
Pour over top of vegetables and allow to marinate at least 24 hours.
Gently turn over with a slotted spoon.
Drain well before serving.
Makes 18 to 20 servings.

title: sugar crumb topping for apples or pie
directions: Blend sugars, flour, salt and butter.
Spoon topping over apples or pies.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fast fruit salad
directions: Take vanilla instant pudding and mix with crushed pineapple left in its juice.
Drain your large can of peaches.
Add to pudding and pineapple mixture.
Cut bananas up and mix well.
Serve right away or chill in refrigerator.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pie filling; stir in milk, lemon juice, marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Grease mold or dish and pour mixture in; put in freezer.

title: draxie's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend margarine and shortening.
Beat in vanilla and eggs. Sift remaining dry ingredients together and add to the sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in the chocolate chips and pecans.

title: bacon biscuits
directions: Cut 1/4 cup shortening into flour.
Stir in 1/2 cup milk and bacon.
Form soft dough and knead.
Pat into 1/2-inch thick round. Cut 4 biscuits with 3 1/2-inch cutter.
Beat egg and brush top with egg. Bake on ungreased sheet 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: roast beef
directions: Put roast into crock-pot.
Sprinkle with Tony's seasoning.
Add onions, carrots and potatoes, if desired.
Cover and let cook on high all day.
Will be fork-tender.
If any leftovers, shred next day and put on top of stove.
Add barbecue sauce and more Tony's. Heat and you have great barbecue sandwiches.

title: molasses crinkles(cookies)
directions: Mix all and roll into balls and then in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Reserve
one cup of the shredded cheese; set aside.
In a large
bowl
combine
the
other ingredients;
spoon
into a lightly
greased 2 1/2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle the reserved cup of	cheese	on top and bake approximately 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch in saucepan over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O and strawberries (Jell-O made by directions on box).
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.
May be topped with whipped cream.
May use cream cheese frosting.

title: canned venison
directions: Cut venison in 2-inch chunks. Soak in 1 tablespoon salt and vinegar for 2 hours. Drain and soak in cold water for 30 minutes. Drain. Pack into jars and add 1/2 teaspoon salt for pints or 1 teaspoon salt for quarts. Pressure can at 10 pounds pressure for 1 hour and 25 minutes for pints or 1 hour and 40 minutes for quarts. Pack jars tightly. No water is needed. Makes its own broth.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Wash
and
cut
rhubarb
in
1/2 to 1-inch slices.
Mix sugar and flour; pour over rhubarb and set aside.
Mix next 4 ingredients
together.
Pour
into
a
or
10-inch pie pan. (Save about 1/2 cup for topping.) Press on bottom and sides to form
a
pie shell.
Put rhubarb mixture in next, then rest of oat mixture on top.
Bake, covered lightly in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Remove top last 10 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook in a saucepan.
Melt the margarine; add the sugar, cocoa, milk and peanut butter.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from stove; add oatmeal and flavoring.
Place on waxed paper with a teaspoon.
Allow to cool and serve.

title: veggie wedgie
directions: Unroll crescent rolls; place on a baking sheet (either round or rectangle).
Bake as instructed on package.
Cool.
Mince/chop veggies.
Combine mayonnaise, cream cheese and dressing mix. Spread mayo mixture on crescent roll base.
Top with veggies and cheese.
Cover and chill.
Slice to serve.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar, then add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture.
Add to this the dates, nuts and cherries.
Roll into balls and roll in cornflake crumbs.
Put on a greased cookie sheet and top each one with a 1/4 piece of cherry.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Put yeast cake in warm water; let stand 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Sift dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Make well in center.
Add shortening.
Mix until consistency of corn meal. Mix yeast in well.
Roll and cut out.
Dip each biscuit in melted oleo.
Place on baking sheet and bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: goulash
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven and brown ground beef until done. Drain and add tomatoes, tomato juice, onion, oregano, pepper, bay leaf and salt to taste.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir in 2 tablespoons margarine, 2 well beaten eggs and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
Press mixture into a 10-inch pie plate or a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Brown 1 pound hamburger or sausage; drain grease and add 1 (15 ounce) jar of your favorite spaghetti sauce.
Spread 1 cup cream-style cottage cheese on top of spaghetti noodles; then spread hamburger mixture over cottage cheese.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle 4 ounces Mozzarella cheese on top and bake for another 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and let set for a few minutes before cutting.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops off pepper, remove seeds and cook for 5 minutes; drain.
Meanwhile in a skillet, brown the onion and meat.
Add the ketchup, salt and pepper; blend well.
Stir in the chips.
Place peppers on shallow baking dish and spoon the meat mixture into them.
Combine the tomato sauce and sugar and spoon half of it over the peppers.
Bake in a 350` oven for 25 minutes.
Spoon the rest of the sauce over the peppers and bake another 10 or 15 minutes.

title: berry patch brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Prepare brownie mix according to package directions. Stir in almonds. Spread batter onto bottom of greased 14-inch pizza pan. Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until set. Cool completely.

title: orange fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges and pineapple and heat to boiling. Add jello and dissolve.
Add cream cheese and let stand for 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients and put in refrigerator.

title: congealed cranberry salad *
