directions: Mix Jell-O and water and let stand until syrupy; add relish and nuts.
Allow to congeal and serve on lettuce.

title: special oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together the first 5 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix well.
Stir in last 4 ingredients and drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crab meltaways
directions: Mix in bowl.
Spread on English muffins.
Freeze 30 minutes. Broil until puffed up and slightly brown.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix together eggs and oil.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toast bread in the toaster until golden brown and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Mix egg yolks, eggs and sugar.
Mix vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg and half and half; add to egg mixture and mix well.
Place cooled cubes in glass pan.
Pour custard over and let soak 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350° until set. Use your toothpick.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Stir in flour.
Stir in 1/2 cup chicken broth and as it thickens, add remaining chicken broth and milk.
Cook to desired consistency and add salt and pepper.

title: california marinade
directions: Mix in quart jar and store in refrigerator.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix together sugar, water, margarine and cinnamon in saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Let boil for 3 min. Set aside.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Mix soup, chiles and Velveeta cheese with 1 cup of chicken broth (add more broth if needed).
Pour 1/4 of this sauce over chicken.
Stir until all the chicken is covered in sauce.
Dip floured tortillas in remaining sauce one at a time, rolling chicken and Cheddar cheese in the tortilla.
Place tortillas in baking dish.
Top with any remaining sauce and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked halibut with cheese sauce
directions: 1. Broil Halibut steaks about 15 minutes. 2. Place in a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. 3. Melt butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Season with salt & pepper. 4. Pour sauce over fish.
Cover with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. 5. Sprinkle with eggs before serving. Serves four.

title: bread and butter pickles(microwave)
directions: Combine cucumbers and onions in a large bowl.
Layer with salt.
Cover with ice and let stand 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Drain and rinse.
(Prepare canning jars and lids according to manufacturer's instructions.)
Combine vinegar, sugar and seasonings in a large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 6 to 7 minutes or until mixture boils, stirring once during cooking time.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Return, covered, to microwave and continue cooking on High until mixture returns to boil, about 12 to 14 minutes, stirring twice during cooking time.
Carefully ladle into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Process jars of pickles for 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine salad dressing and milk; mix in remaining ingredients. Pour into shallow pan; cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: caramel pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar with flour; add beaten egg yolks and milk. Blend thoroughly and bring mixture to a boil.
Meanwhile, brown 1 cup sugar in iron skillet, stirring constantly, until melted.
Add caramelized sugar, while hot, to hot milk mixture.
Cook in double boiler or heavy pan until thick.
Add about 3 tablespoons butter. Beat smooth and pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Make meringue with egg whites; spread on pies and bake in oven until golden brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch lightly greased baking dish. Pour broth over chicken.
Spread the undiluted soup over chicken and broth.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix melted butter, flour and milk.
Pour evenly over soup.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until brown crust forms.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: perfect penuche fudge
directions: Boil together sugars, cornstarch and milk until it forms a soft-ball in cold water.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla, butter and nuts.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Pour into buttered pan (10 1/2 x 7-inches).

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix
all
together.
Cover
with
Reynolds Wrap for 1st hour. Remove
wrapper and cook for 1 1/2 hours or until done. Bake at 300°.

title: swiss corn bake
directions: Combine ingredients
and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix and pour half in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake 20 minutes. While baking, melt 1 package Kraft caramels and the other half can Eagle Brand milk.
Pour over cake.
Add small package chocolate chips and 1 cup pecans.
Pour remaining batter on top and bake 20 to 30 minutes more.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: frosty fruit pie
directions: Bring to boil first 2 ingredients.
Stir in until dissolved the gelatin.
Mix in sugar.
Cool until almost stiff.
Whip until stiff the milk with lemon juice.* Pour on top of gelatin mixture.
Beat in slowly with mixer at low speed.
Pour into baked pie shell. Chill at least 1 hour.

title: easy chicken cacciatore
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender. Add remaining ingredients except chicken and wine.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes. Stir in chicken and wine. Simmer, covered, 30 minutes. Serve on hot cooked spaghetti.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli according to directions on package.
When half tender, remove from pan and place in bottom of baking pan. Sprinkle contents of Stove Top dressing over broccoli (both packets).
Dilute soup with cup of milk; bring to boiling point. Pour gently over broccoli and dressing.
Dot margarine and then sprinkle with cheese.
(Any cheese of your choice will do).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not add salt to cooking broccoli, as dressing is seasoned.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Sift together 2 tablespoons cocoa and 1 cup powdered sugar. Combine and stir bourbon and corn syrup.
Add and mix thoroughly crushed vanilla wafers and nut meat.
Roll mixture into small balls.
Dredge in 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 1 tablespoon cocoa that have been mixed together.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and salt.
Add flour, spices and baking powder.
Beat egg yolks separately.
Add honey, milk, figs (or raisins) and almonds.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake slowly in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost with boiled icing.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt Crisco and brown mushrooms.
Add flour and stir until blended.
Slowly add stock.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add chicken, salt and cayenne.
Cook until chicken is hot.
Add a little of the sauce to egg yolks and return to rest of mixture.
Continue stirring over heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in pimentos.
Serve hot over rice or biscuits.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and
chop strawberries into jello. Add pineapple and nuts.
Put half of
the mixture in a dish
and let jell.
Put sour cream over
the
first	mixture, spread evenly.
Put remaining mixture of strawberries over the sour cream and let jell (Use a 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish).

title: party punch
directions: Mix jell-o according to package directions. When mixed well add both cans of juice, stir well, chill and serve. Makes approximately 3 gallons.

title: harry's sauerkraut balls
directions: Simmer butter or margarine, onion and garlic.
Add and simmer corned beef, sauerkraut, seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce. Blend beef stock, egg and flour.
Stir in first mixture until thick; remove from heat and, after cooling off, chill in refrigerator at least 12 to 15 hours.

Shape this mixture in walnut size balls, then make a mixture of 2 cups milk and 2 1/2 cups flour; dip the balls in this, then roll in bread crumbs. Deep fry in hot oil for 2 to 3 minutes or until the balls swim on top.
Drain on paper towel and don't eat for about 2 minutes. Don't fry more than one dozen at a time.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: calico salad
directions: Heat together vinegar, pepper, salt, sugar and oil until dissolved; set aside to cool.
Place vegetables in large bowl or container and pour cooled dressing over vegetable mixture. Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours or overnight.
Add more vegetables to marinade when supply gets low.

title: hot peach tea
directions: Mix well.
To serve add 3 rounded teaspoons of the mixture to 1 cup hot water.

title: (spam) ham casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Put in casserole dish and add butter, 5 slices of cheese and half of Cheddar cheese; mix until cheeses are melted.
Add Accent, soup, milk, egg and diced meat. Season to taste.
Place remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 400° until top is brown.

title: auntie rox's midnight torte
directions: In double boiler, over medium-high heat, melt chocolate and butter together.
Place mixture into medium mixing bowl.
Wash top of double boiler.

title: emily's potatoes
directions: Pour dressing mixture over potatoes evenly.
Put foil on pan for 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Take foil off after 15 minutes and continue to cook for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time. Mix flour and baking powder.
Add vanilla to milk.
Add flour mixture and milk mixture alternately.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn heat to 325°.
Bake 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes before turning out.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Keep broth.
Add bouillon cubes to broth.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine sugar, shortening, salt and boiling water in bowl; mix well.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and eggs; beat well.
Add flour; mix well.
Chill, covered with greased wax paper, for up to 10 days.
Roll to desired thickness on floured surface; cut as desired.
Place on greased sheet.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: chocolate raspberry ice cream
directions: Heat whipping cream.

Beat yolks and sugar together. Gradually add hot cream to yolk mixture, whisking constantly. Cook mixture in top of double boiler over simmering water, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens slightly and coats the back of a spoon, about 8 minutes.
Do not let mixture boil. Remove from heat.
Strain mixture into bowl.
Add chocolate and vanilla, stirring occasionally, until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Cool completely.
Stir raspberries with juice into cooled mixture.
Freeze in ice cream freezer according to manufacturer's instructions.
Spoon ice cream into serving dishes. Garnish with fresh raspberries if available.

title: apple-cheddar tart
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare Cheddar Pastry.
Roll out pastry dough to 12-inch circle.
Place in 10-inch tart pan with removable bottom or 10-inch quiche dish; trim pastry and flute edges, sealing to side of pan.
Prick bottom and sides of pastry with fork.
Beat egg white until frothy; brush lightly over bottom of pastry.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Chill one hour before serving.
Dip with Tostitos chips.

title: sausage hot dog chili
directions: Brown sausage, hot dogs, onion and green pepper in large skillet.
Pour off fat; add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Makes around six to eight servings.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Combine milk and peanut butter, blending well. Add pudding mix and beat for 1 minute. Spoon at once into cooled pie shell. Chill 2 hours. Can be served with Cool Whip.

title: honey and vinegar cough syrup(home remedies)
directions: In an enamel pan, boil rapidly for 2 minutes the sugar, honey and vinegar.
Remove from heat. Add the butter. Add the ginger (optional).
Keep warm and take as needed.

title: salmon dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: caramel candy
directions: Put sugar, Karo syrup and margarine in saucepan.
Boil until it spins a thread from the spoon.
Pour in milk.
Stir until candy thermometer reads 240°.
Put in salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in greased pan and cool.
Cut in squares.

title: cold lemon chicken
directions: Melt butter and saute chicken breasts until golden brown. Remove to a heavy casserole with cover.
Add vermouth to skillet and reduce juices to approximately 1/3 cup.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/3 cup lemon juice, salt and pepper to skillet.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until just tender.
Baste if necessary, adding more vermouth.

title: shrimp fra diavolo
directions: Saute garlic in oil until brown; add parsley, tomatoes, basil and oregano and cook on medium heat for 30 minutes.
Put shrimp in sauce; add white wine, cheese and crushed pepper.
Cook until firm, about 7 minutes.
Serve over linguini.

title: orange pineapple pretzel salad
directions: Mix and press pretzels, sugar and oleo into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Dissolve jello with water; add pineapple (drained), then add 7-Up or Sprite. Refrigerate until partially set.
Pour jello mixture over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate.

title: yeast biscuits(fried yeast bread)
directions: Mix well and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Dough may be stored for up to 3 weeks in fridge.

title: fruit topping for angel food cake
directions: Drain and quarter peach halves; cut strawberries in half. Toss all ingredients together and let stand 30 minutes.
Spoon over slices of cake and serve immediately.

title: soy sauce dressing for salads
directions: Mix together.
So good over lettuce salads.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Chill until firm.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in nuts.
Wrap in foil; place in fridge overnight.
Sprinkle with paprika; slice to serve.

title: mexican salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together except corn chips and dressing. Chill.
Add chips and dressing at serving time.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Thoroughly mix fruit and sugar in a large bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix water and fruit pectin in small saucepan; boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit. Continue stirring for 3 minutes.

title: low-fat pasta primavera
directions: Cook onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons broth 5 to 7 minutes or until softened.
Add tomato sauce, honey and spices and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Saute red pepper, zucchini, mushrooms, carrots and broccoli in 2 tablespoons broth until tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Add peas and stir-fry 2 more minutes.
Add vegetables to sauce.
Add balsamic vinegar and cook 15 minutes.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: veal pot roast
directions: Combine dry ingredients; spread on waxed paper.
Roll meat on both sides.

title: none such prize cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda; cream shortening and add sugar gradually.
Cream together until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Add mincemeat, broken into small pieces.
Add flour and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 12 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies 3 inches in diameter.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef and onion in a little oil. Add catsup, Worcestershire sauce, water, vinegar, paprika, tomato sauce, garlic salt, mustard, salt and pepper. Simmer for 30 minutes. Serve on heated hamburger buns.

title: chocolate mint cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda; cut in oleo until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of
13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: diabetic sweet-sour cabbage
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add cabbage, using only the water which still clings to the leaves.
Cook, covered, over low heat until tender, stirring occasionally, to prevent sticking. Add onion rings, water, vinegar and Sucaryl.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes longer.
Yields 6 servings at 68 calories per serving.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In large pan, cook and stir meat and onion in butter until meat is brown and onion is tender. Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms. Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in soup. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream and heat through. Serve over noodles.

title: simply sensational cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and shortening; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Beat in eggs and lemon juice.
Pour into prepared pan; bake 45 minutes or until center is set.
Top with sour cream.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool.
Chill.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: poached salmon with horseradish sauce
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large skillet; bring to boil over medium heat.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Add salmon steaks.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove skillet from heat and let stand 8 minutes.
Remove salmon steak to serving plate; serve with horseradish sauce.
Yields 4 servings.

title: squash or mirliton custard pie
directions: *Or mix 1 cup flour, 1/2 teaspoon baking powder and 1/8 teaspoon salt.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with green pepper and onion.
Add tomatoes and soup.
Cook spaghetti; drain well and add to hamburger mixture. Place in a greased casserole dish and cover with cheese.
Bake one can (10) biscuits for 5 minutes on a cookie sheet.
Place biscuits on top of casserole and bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until brown.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350° and grease a 6 cup rectangular baking dish. In small saucepan, make white sauce:
Melt butter; add flour and stir until smooth.
Do not allow to brown.
Continue stirring, whisk while adding milk.
Bring just to a boil over low heat. Remove from heat and whisk beaten eggs.
Stir in cheeses and seasoning.
Pour into dish.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.
Taste may be changed by substituting Swiss, Cheddar or Gruyere cheese.
A crowd pleaser.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Crumble Ritz crackers over top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows, oil and butter.
Remove from heat and add gumdrops and nuts.
Then add enough popcorn to fill an angel food cake pan.
Mix all together and place in a greased angel food cake pan.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: edna's casserole
directions: Saut meat in small amount of oil.
Add onions and pepper. Cook until almost done.
Add remaining ingredients, except noodles and cheese.
Cook mixture for 45 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and add along with the cheese sauce mixture.
Pour into a covered baking dish and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; fold in Cool Whip.
Cover and freeze.

title: pineapple-cheese salad
directions: Stir
cream
cheese, sugar and salad dressing together. Blend in pineapple.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill in fridge until ready to serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Place melted butter in casserole dish.
Combine bread mix, onion, eggs, corns and sour cream.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie muffins
directions: Pour into a well-greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle the 3/4 cup reserved crumb mixture on top before baking.
Bake at 350 degrees until top is golden brown and cake tests done.
(Glass pan -- 325 degrees.)

title: tea sandwiches
directions: Chill cans of date nut bread at least four hours.
Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Drain pineapple and reserve the liquid.

Mix cream cheese and pineapple to a spreadable consistency using as much of the liquid as needed. Slice bread. Make sandwiches and then cut them in half; chill until ready to serve. Arrange on a serving tray.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil water, butter, shortening and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix quickly.
Pour into greased 9 x 14 pan and bake 25 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: ground beef grand style
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Combine cream cheese, soup and milk.
Add salt, beef and catsup.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Place biscuits on top.
Bake another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Bring last 3 ingredients to boil. Roll 1 slice apple in each roll. Put into a greased 9 x 13 pan. Pour syrup over rolls; pour 1 can or 8 to 10 ounces Mountain Dew over rolls. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Put small amount of Cool Whip on top before serving.

title: baked chicken with yellow rice
directions: Sprinkle paprika on chicken.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken placed in a baking dish.
Let stand about 30 minutes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Turn unit higher for the last 5 minutes to brown.
Serve over yellow rice.

title: aunt mary troop's spinach salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and whirl for about 20 seconds.
This can	be
stored
in	your
refrigerator up to 2 months.
Ours never lasts
that
long as we love it and use it on tossed salad too.
Delicious!

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Drain mixed vegetables until all liquid is gone.
Mix first 4 ingredients together in medium bowl.
Top with corn flakes or crushed crackers.
Melt margarine and pour over top of casserole. Bake at 325° until corn flakes or crackers are brown and casserole is bubbling.

title: aunt florie's red velvet cake
directions: You will also need a large piece of cardboard, aluminum foil and 1 large aluminum or stainless steel mixing bowl.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs, milk, ketchup, salt and pepper. Add beef and mix well. Put half of meat mixture in greased 9 X 5 X 3 pan. Set aside. Saute mushrooms and onions in butter until tender, about 3 minutes. Add breadcrumbs, parsley, thyme, salt and pepper. Saute until crumbs are lightly browned. Spoon over meat mixture. Cover with remaining meat mixture and press down gently. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Drain fat when necessary.

title: hearty tortilla chip soup
directions: Microwave Directions:
Combine onion, carrots and garlic in 3 quart microwave safe casserole.
Cover with vented plastic wrap or lid; microwave on high (100% power) 7 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Finely crush half the tortilla chips.
Add crushed chips, broth, water, salsas and tomato paste; stir well.
Cover; microwave on High 6 minutes or until soup bubbles.
Microwave on Medium (50% power) 6 minutes.
To serve, divide remaining tortilla chips and half the cheese among 6 individual soup bowls.
Ladle soup over cheese and chips, dividing evenly.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Crumble cold biscuits, no certain amount, depends on size dish you are using.
Instead of using water, I replace it with milk. Pour milk over biscuits; let set for awhile for biscuits to soak up liquid.
Add other ingredients.
Mix together.
The ingredients would need to be adjusted for a large pudding.
Bake in oven at 400° to 450° until pudding browns.

title: chicken crescent almondine
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in pan; cook until bubbly.
Pour in a baking dish.
Roll out can of crescent rolls; do not separate.
Put on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with 2/3 cup grated Swiss cheese and 1/2 cup slivered almonds.
Pour on top 2 to 4 tablespoons melted oleo.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: lenten filaef(palestinian)
directions: Into a large pot, put rice, lentils, salt and water.
Bring to a boil, cover tightly, turn heat to low and steam until tender.

title: fry bread
directions: Mix water, yeast, sugar and salt.
Let set a few minutes.
Add flour and oil.
When mixed pinch off small ball.
Take hands and stretch dough.
Fry in oil.

title: black walnut pudding
directions: Mix the ingredients for the syrup and boil on low heat. Pour into 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: sour cream puffs
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening. Add sour cream and stir until dough clings together.
Pat out on floured surface to 1/2-inch thick.
With a large cutter, cut 6 to 8 biscuits 2 1/2-inches round.
Cut 6 to 8 more 1-inch round and place on top of larger ones.
Brush with remaining sour cream and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes. Try as biscuits or top any casserole or stew instead of dumplings.

title: enchilada verde
directions: Melt margarine in pan; add flour to make paste.
Add chicken broth to make heavy sauce.
When thick, add green chilies and sour cream.
Saute tortillas in skillet.
Fill tortillas with chopped onions and cheese.
Place in pan and pour sauce over top; sprinkle with cheese.
May add chicken to filling for tortillas.
Place in a 425° oven for 20 minutes.

title: pecan dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend in milk and sour cream.
Add pepper, onion and garlic.
Fold in dried beef and put in pie tin. Melt butter and mix in nuts well.
Spread over top of cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken and sweet basil italiano
directions: In large skillet, fill bottom of skillet 1/4-inch with olive oil. Saute onions until tender. Add black olives, garlic and chicken. Cook until tender. Salt and pepper to taste. Add tomatoes; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Add cheese. In separate pan, cook 1/2 pound angel hair pasta al dent. Drain. Pour meat mixture over pasta. Sprinkle with light dusting of Parmesan cheese.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix together; let stand in refrigerator.
Will keep for some time.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Dredge chicken in flour and brown in butter.
Place in baking dish.
Put
a little more butter in frying pan and brown mushrooms.
Add wine and bring to boil.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: gingerbread cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and molasses.
Stir dry ingredients and add.
Chill.
Roll out not too thin.
Bake at 350° until dry, not crisp.
Makes enough dough to make one small castle or many shaped cookies.
Frost, if desired.

title: fat city squares
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup milk and nuts.
Stir until dough holds together.
Press half of the dough in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. (Save remaining dough for top.)
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, peel and grate potatoes.
In medium saucepan melt butter and add cheese.
Melt over low heat.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream.
Add chopped green onions, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Stir lightly and pour into casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pat into a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix the cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar and spread on top of cake mixture. Bake at 325° to 350° until set (approximately 15 to 20 minutes).

title: cajun chicken 'n rice
directions: Skin chicken and cover with salt, pepper and red pepper.
Put about 2 teaspoons oil in big pot.
Put chicken in it and let it brown.
Meanwhile, chop up veggies, then add them to pot and let them brown too.
(Takes about 20 to 25 minutes to brown.)
Pour tomato sauce in and cover chicken with water.
Put lid on pot and let it boil about 50 minutes.
Make as much rice as you want, then take out chicken pieces and slightly thicken leftover gravy with Wondra.

title: stir-fry chicken with vegetables
directions: Heat oil in skillet or wok.
Add garlic and zucchini and cook over high heat, stirring quickly and frequently, until zucchini is cooked but slightly crisp, about 1 minute.
Add the chicken, onion and bell pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the chicken is heated through and the vegetables are tender-crisp (2 to 3 minutes).
Add the tomatoes and soy sauce; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thoroughly heated, 1 to 2 minutes more.
Makes 2 servings.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Cook slowly until thick.
Add red food coloring.
Fold into fresh strawberries.
Place in baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, vanilla and 1/2 of cake mix until smooth.
Stir in remainder of mix and coconut.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on cookie sheet, greased.
Important to stir in last half of cake mix.
Bake 7 minutes until light brown.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.
Sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar and seal tightly.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar. Let stand. Dissolve Jell-O in warm water. Chill. Add celery, nuts, oranges and cranberries when Jell-O begins to set up.

title: turkey spaghetti
directions: Brown turkey with some butter, onion and garlic; don't overcook.
When turkey is browned, add can of soup; mix well. Then add 1 or 2 cups of cheese; depends on how much you like. Cook spaghetti until done.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together; mixture should be fairly coarse.
The secret to this is to mix 1/2 cup cold water and 1/4 cup flour and add to the above mixture.

title: tuna noodle casserole(heart at work recipe; slimmed down favorite)
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on the package, omitting salt.
Rinse and drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Saute onion and garlic until onion is transparent, 2 to 3 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: french dressing from circle drive
directions: Mix and shake well.
Makes about one quart.

title: date nut bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Cool, then add all other ingredients.
Beat well and bake in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hearty chicken bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine potatoes, half the cheese and half the onions; mix thoroughly.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, spreading across bottom and up sides to form shell.
In a large bowl, combine chicken, mixed vegetables, soup, milk and seasonings.
Pour into potato shell.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake uncovered 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in oil; drain.
Grease casserole dish. Place half of tortillas in dish.
Add small amount of meat, cheese and chili peppers.
Repeat in layers.
Dilute soup with milk and pour over top.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased casserole. Bake in 375 oven for 40 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Combine beef and onions in soup pot.
Cook over medium high heat until meat is lightly browned.
Add seasoning, tomatoes, pork and beans, and water.
Cook over medium heat for about 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender; drain and rinse. Make white sauce of margarine, flour, milk and seasonings; add 2/3 cheese; stir until melted.
Pour over macaroni in oiled or Pam-sprayed baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and crumbs over top.
Bake in 325° oven 30 minutes.
If desired, make tomato macaroni by adding 1 1/2 cups cooked tomatoes or canned tomatoes after macaroni is added.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions.
Pour batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Poke holes with a straw or ice pick.
Pour condensed milk over cake.
Pour cream of coconut over condensed milk.
Spread Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut.
Chill.

title: pineapple, carrot, raisin muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger.
Stir in carrots, raisins and nuts.

title: german stuffed cabbage
directions: Start large kettle boiling water.
Cut hearts out of whole cabbage heads.
Put cabbage in boiling water long enough to separate leaves.
While cabbage is in water, mix ground turkey, ground steak, eggs, onion, garlic, rice, salt and pepper.
Put approximately 1/4 cup meat mixture in cabbage leaf; roll, then poke in ends using approximately 1/2 meat mixture.
Use remaining portion meat mixture to make meat balls.
Chop remaining cabbage and put chopped cabbage, rolls and balls into large kettle.
Add tomatoes, juice and puree; cook until done, approximately 5 to 6 hours.

title: homestyle chicken and biscuit dumplings
directions: Shake flour in oven cooking bag.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add gravy mix, garlic powder and water.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.
Place carrots and celery in bag in an even layer.
Sprinkle chicken with seasoning.
Place on top of vegetables.
Arrange biscuits around chicken.
Close bag and bake chicken until tender, 50 to 55 minutes.

title: anna's bran muffins
directions: Mix with wooden spoon dry ingredients.
Add the beaten eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Cover and store in refrigerator overnight. Fill muffin tins 2/3.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Mix can be stored in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: unusual conserve
directions: Cut 8 cups rhubarb in 1-inch pieces.
Simmer for 8 minutes and add 8 cups sugar.
Cook together for 15 more minutes.
Set off stove and add 3 boxes of jello.
Skim and stir.
Pour into hot jars and seal with paraffin wax.
Makes 6 jars or more.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Blend together above ingredients except chips.
Add the chips and set aside.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Serve on your choice of crackers.

title: sausage - pineapple hot sandwiches
directions: Place English muffin halves on greased baking pan.
Fry sausage, breaking into small bits, until cooked through and browned.
Pour off excess fat; add seasonings and pineapple. Spread muffins with tomato paste; add layer of sausage mixture. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Wash and boil potatoes in salted water until soft or bake in oven until done.
Peel and mash.
Add butter, sugar, juice and rind to hot potatoes.
Beat until light (as creamed potatoes). Preheat oven to 350°.
Place in 2-quart casserole and bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with a topping of marshmallows.
Put back in oven for a few minutes to brown toppings.
Serves 8.

title: tuck me to sleep cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Divide dough and shape into rolls. Wrap; chill in refrigerator overnight.
In the morning, slice to desired thickness.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° to 400° until light brown.

title: never fail pie dough
directions: Blend lard, salt and flour.
Add water.
Work in a little more flour with hands if too sticky.

title: one minute chocolate icing
directions: Mix together and bring to a slow boil.
When it starts to boil, let it boil exactly one minute.
Remove from heat and beat until thick enough to spread.

title: plantation frost
directions: In a covered blender container at high speed, blend coffee, sugar and banana until mixture is smooth, about 20 seconds.
Add ice cream; reduce speed to medium and blend until smooth, about 10 seconds.
To serve, pour into chilled 8 ounce glasses.

title: basic banana pudding
directions: Mix egg yolks, milk, 1 1/2 cups sugar and flour.
Cook in double boiler until medium thick.
Let cool.
Layer wafers and bananas in large Pyrex dish.
Pour milk mixture over.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add remaining sugar and flavoring.
Spread over pudding.
Brown in 350° oven until golden brown.
Yields 10 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter a 9-inch square pan.
Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Beat eggs.
Stir in buttermilk, corn, bacon drippings, onion, bacon, 1/2 cup of cheese and chilies; add to cornmeal mixture.
Stir until well combined.
Add to cornmeal mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered pan; sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: almond paste cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and flavoring until light and fluffy. Add egg and almond paste; blend well.
Add sifted flour and dry ingredients.
Chill dough 2 hours or more.
Form into balls, 1 teaspoon per cookie.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down gently with bottom of small juice glass that has been dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until delicately golden brown.
Watch carefully as they are thin and burn quickly.

title: professor's squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender. Drain. Add remaining ingredients, topping with crumbs.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour or longer at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Spread over top of meat loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and bran and mix together.
Combine water and bananas.
Add to mixture, alternating with sifted dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour in a wax paper lined 5 x 9-inch pan.
(Grease and flour sides of baking pan; any 100% bran may be used.)

title: on top of stove cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil. Combine remaining ingredients and add to the first mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool.

title: veal scallops in mustard sauce
directions: Saute veal on both sides over high heat.
Remove from pan. To same pan, add shallot, cream, Vermouth, mustard, butter, Worcestershire sauce (to taste) and brandy (to taste).
Reduce to half over medium to low heat.
Pour over veal and serve.

title: chicken ginger from thailand
directions: Saute chicken in oil with all ingredients.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons of water if ingredients dry out.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Keep popcorn warm in 300° oven.
Cook sugar and water, salt and corn syrup to hard boil at 256°.
Add vinegar and vanilla. Cook to light crack (270°).
Pour slowly over popcorn.
Mix well. Press into balls.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Butter and eggs should be at room temperature.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking soda together; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Beat in vanilla, coconut and nuts. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour into pan and bake 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Test middle.
Cool and ice with Cream Cheese Frosting (recipe in this book).

title: pumpkin crunch dessert
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with waxed paper.
Mix together salt, pumpkin, milk, sugar, cinnamon and eggs.
Pour into waxed pan. Sprinkle all over the cake mix.
Pour margarine over dry cake mix. Cover cake with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool down 10 minutes.
Flip upside down onto a platter or cake board.
It will be soft at first.
It firms up as it cools.
Put in refrigerator for 4 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: spanish chicken and rice(crock-pot)
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in crock-pot on low all day.
Remove chicken at end of day and shred, then return to crock-pot.
Thirty minutes before serving, add uncooked rice and continue cooking on low.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and sour cream.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: In a small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over 1/2 cup water; let stand for 1 minute.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is clear.
Cool to room temperature.
In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, orange juice concentrate, orange liqueur and gelatin mixture; mix well. Spoon into graham crackers crust, smoothing the top.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.
Hull strawberries and cut in halves; arrange over pie.
In a small saucepan, place currant jelly and 1 teaspoon water.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Spoon over strawberries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: quick and easy crackers
directions: Blend the mayonnaise, onion and garlic powder together. Spread the mixture on the crackers and sprinkle with Parmesan. Place on a broiler proof dish.
Broil until the cheese melts. Serve immediately.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with water over low heat or in double boiler. Stir whipped topping into chocolate.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill.

title: uncle bobby's yogurt bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add yogurt and honey; mix. Put into small, greased bread pan.
Sprinkle sesame or poppy seed on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator.
It tastes better after it sets in refrigerator for a couple of days.

title: meaty ziti
directions: Cook ziti and drain.
In small mixing bowl, mix the chopped onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
In small pan, stir the meat until brown and then strain.
In the same small pan, mix the Spatini and paste according to the directions on the packet of Spatini.
Add the meat and let simmer.
In small casserole dish or oblong pan, place the ziti, top with meat, then with cheese, until all of the ingredients are gone (this can be layered if preferred).
Bake in the oven at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until cheese is nice and golden.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in greased pan.
Cover each breast with slice of cheese.
Mix soup and sherry and pour over chicken.
Cover with stuffing.
Melt margarine and pour over stuffing.
Cover with foil; bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake another 15 to 20 minutes, until chicken is cooked.

title: crabmeat dip(big hit at parties!)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add crabmeat.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese and bake 15 minutes more.
I stir it again when I take it out of oven.
Serve with crackers.
Serve hot.

title: flounder florentine
directions: Place fish fillets in 1 cup boiling water.
Cook, uncovered, 2 minutes.
Drain.
Place spinach and onion in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Separate spinach with fork.
When water returns to boiling, cover and cook spinach 2 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix with marjoram.

title: rum fudge pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs and blend.
Slowly add butter, then nuts and extracts.
Bake in well-greased 9-inch Pyrex pie plate for 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine milk and egg. Mix well.
Add Bisquick mix, parsley, onions, half of cheese and oleo.
Mix well.
Spoon into a greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fern's peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar together until smooth. Add peanut butter and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 9-inch graham cracker crust or a baked pastry shell.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Beat eggs, and then add milk and corn bread mix. Add remaining ingredients; mix well and pour into preheated and greased baking pan or large skillet. Top with cheese. Bake 35 minutes at 400 degrees or until top is golden brown.

title: barbecued spareribs in crock-pot
directions: Trim fat from spareribs and salt and pepper them.
Broil for 10 minutes on each side.
Slice onions and place on bottom of crock-pot (optional).
Put spareribs on top of onions.
Pour barbecue sauce over the ribs. Cook in the crock-pot on low for 8 hours.

title: cheese krispie appetizers
directions: Beat cheese and butter together.
Add flour and seasonings. Fold in Rice Krispies.
Put dough on waxed paper and form into a cylinder, about 12 x 1 1/2-inches.
Wrap and refrigerate overnight. Preheat oven to 375°.
Slice.
Roll into 1/4-inch slices.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Can be made ahead and frozen up to a month.
Contains 45 calories each.

title: black olive cream cheese dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and olives together.
Add a little liquid to soften, but do not add too much or it will be too runny and soft. This is great with chips.

title: white icing
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup until it reaches the soft-ball stage in cold water. Whip eggs stiff. Pour syrup gradually over whites, beating with electric beater until of spreading consistency. This icing pours instead of your having
to spread it on cake.

title: fillet of flounder divan
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter 2-quart baking dish.
Separate broccoli.
Arrange in bottom of dish.
Cut fillets into 4 pieces each and brush with lemon juice.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Arrange fish over broccoli.
Spoon Sauce over fish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: savory baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in well greased small baking dish. Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
This is delicious with baked ham or meat loaf.

title: foolproof roast beef
directions: Rub roast with seasonings; let stand until room temperature. Place in roasting pan.
Preheat oven to 375° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven.
Do not open oven door.
Do not remove from oven.
Before serving, turn on oven again at 375°; bake an additional 30 to 40 minutes.
No matter what size, it will be brown on outside, but rare to medium inside.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Sift spices and flour well together. Add to creamed mixture.
Add soda to applesauce and add to mixture last with gumdrops and fruit which have been added to part of the flour.
To keep moist, set a container of water in oven while baking. Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour. This makes a big cake.
I bake it in a Bundt pan.

title: world famous potato salad
directions: Put egg yolks in small bowl and mash with fork, adding pickle juice and very small amount mustard.
Add sour cream, mayonnaise and possibly more pickle juice until right consistency.
Chop up egg whites, add along with all other listed ingredients to cooked, drained potatoes.
Then add mayo/dressing mixture and you might need some salt (taste to see).
Mix well together with hands.

title: quickie homemade rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into muffin pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 400° until brown.
Makes 6 muffins.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Spread rice and onion soup mix in bottom of large casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of that.
Mix soups and water together and pour over rice and chicken.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix together until smooth the cream cheese and sour cream; spread evenly in shallow round dish or pie plate.
Mix salsa and taco seasoning; spread on top of cheese/sour cream mixture.
Top with chopped vegetables of choice.
Serve with nachos.

title: arabian stew
directions: Sear pork chops on both sides in a hot frying pan; then remove to a casserole dish.
On each pork chop place 1 tablespoon of rice, a slice of onion, a slice of tomato (or the equivalent in stewed tomatoes) and 2 strips of green peppers.
Sprinkle with pepper and salt.
Add the hot water, cover and bake 3 to 4 hours in a 350° oven.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Beat milk for 1 minute.
Add Kool-Aid and sugar.
Beat until thick.
Place wafers in dish.
Pour milk mixture over wafers. Stand wafers around sides of dish. Freeze until firm.

title: chicken casserole with almonds
directions: Boil chicken.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Mix sour cream, soups and almonds with chicken.
Put in buttered baking dish. Cover with cracker crumbs and sprinkle 1 teaspoon poppy seed over crackers.
Pour melted butter over.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, usually 30 to 45 minutes.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Place butter and brown sugars in a medium size saucepan over medium heat.
Stir and cook about 2 minutes or until the mixture comes to a boil.
Add milk; stir and bring the mixture back to a boil.
Remove pan from heat.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla. Beat with a wooden spoon until the frosting is smooth.
Use right away while still warm to frost the cake of your choice or the frosting will harden.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Mix all above ingredients together.
Serve as a dip or spread on bread for finger sandwiches.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, cocoa, sugar and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Break noodles in thirds, cook, drain and rinse.
Add onion and celery to noodles and mix lightly.
Mix seasoning with italian dressing and add to noodle mixture; cover and chill overnight. Garnish with tops of celery and sprigs of parsley just before serving.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix as usual.
Refrigerate several hours.
Roll on floured surface and cut to desired shapes.
Bake until light brown at 350°.
These puff up some and stay soft.
Ice.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add taco seasoning as directed on seasoning package.
Set aside.
Prepare dough and place in a deep dish pan.
Place in hot oven at 400° until light brown, then place meat mixture and cheese on top of crust.
Repeat until mixture is gone, then bake until cheese melts, then top with lettuce, onion, tomatoes, taco sauce and sour cream.
Serve warm.

title: persimmon-black walnut bread
directions: Sift flour and soda together.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add well beaten eggs and combine with flour mixture. Add persimmon pulp and nuts.
Line pans with greased waxed paper (2 loaf pans).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding with 1 to 2 cups orange and pineapple juice as liquid, depending on amount of fruit being used.
Cool overnight. Mix pudding with fruit.
Serve topped with Cool Whip.
Garnish with angel food cake wedge or decorative cookie.

title: good hash brown potato dish
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in large casserole dish. Mix onions, sour cream, hash brown, chicken soup, cheese, salt and pepper. Pour this over melted margarine. Mix together 4 Tbsp. melted margarine and crushed corn flakes. Spread over top and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf and sauce
directions: Heat and pour over meat loaf.

title: pan roasted chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken thoroughly.
Melt butter with oil in large skillet.
When butter foams, add chicken pieces, garlic and rosemary.
Brown chicken on all sides over medium heat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add wine.
When wine is reduced by half, partially cover skillet.
Cook over medium heat 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Place chicken on warm platter.
If sauce looks dry, stir in a little more wine.
If sauce is too thin, increase heat and boil, uncovered, until it reaches desired thickness.
Remove most of fat from sauce.
Taste and adjust sauce for seasoning, then spoon over chicken.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Set aside potatoes, onion and celery.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Then mix all the ingredients together and let it chill several hours.
This is best the second day. Serves 4.

title: mock apple slices
directions: Peel and seed zucchini; slice thin.
Cook zucchini in lemon juice until tender.
Add 1 1/4 cups sugar, nutmeg and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Simmer a few minutes.
Combine flour, salt, 2 cups sugar and margarine as for pie crust.
Use 1/2 cup of crumb mixture to thicken zucchini.
Cool.

title: pinto bean pie(poor boy pecan pie)
directions: Combine beans, sugar, butter, and eggs (mix with a spoon). Stir in coconut and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell, and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: roast beef
directions: Wash roast; rub with seasonings and Worcestershire sauce.
In a large crock-pot add vegetables to roast and water.
Cook for 5 to 8 hours, depending on size of roast.

title: appetizer
directions: Wrap bacon around water chestnut; put toothpick through.
Put in deep pan.
Cook at 350° until bacon is done.
Take out; pour mixture over bacon.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Serve cold or warm; very good.

title: coffee pecan chews
directions: Sift together the flour, coffee and salt.
In bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar; beat until stiff.
Stir in melted butter and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Put in an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sandies
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar.
Add
water and vanilla; mix well. Add
flour	and
pecans.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Shape in fingers or balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes. Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: my mom's dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter or margarine.
Remove from heat.
Add cornbread and bread crumbs.
Add egg and seasonings. Add broth.
Mixture will be watery.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until top is brown and dressing doesn't wiggle when shaken.
Don't overcook. Tastes even better rewarmed.
Freezes well.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate Cracker Barrel cheese.
Let cream cheese and grated Cracker Barrel come to room temperature.
Mix with wooden spoon (or hands) all ingredients except nuts.
Roll into a large ball or divide into two. Roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until chilled and serve with crackers.

title: peanut cluster
directions: Heat sugar, butter and milk to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Cook 3 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Mix in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Drop on wax paper.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Put the butter, peanut butter, white and brown sugar and egg in large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; stir these dry ingredients into contents of bowl.
Chill the dough for one hour or more; roll heaping teaspoonfuls between the floured palm of hands to make balls.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with underside of floured fork, pressing twice to make a crisscross pattern.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sallie m. russell's lemon pie
directions: Mix
together
the
sugar
and
flour,
then
add milk. Gradually add
beaten egg yolks.
Stir in lemon rind and juice and cook
over medium heat until thick.
Take from stove.
Add butter and
let
stand until butter melts.
Place in baked pie shell. Add meringue and bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and roll into small balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour half of batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk and melted oleo.
Blend mixture well and pour over cake.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup nuts and chocolate chips over caramel mixture.
Pour remaining batter over cake and sprinkle with nuts.

title: la crema(cream)
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Place in double boiler. Stir constantly until wooden spoon becomes coated.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and pour over ladyfingers or sponge cake, cut into pieces.

title: summer cool cake
directions: Mix cake and bake as directed.
Cool completely in pan.
Blend jello according to directions.
Pour slowly over cake.
Cool in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours overnight.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle to decorate.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs. Beat well.
Add salt, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add apples.
Beat well. Add flour.
Beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours or until done at 325°.

title: popeye's biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Melt margarine in a baking dish. Knead mixture after placing on additional Bisquick mix.
Roll out or cut biscuits.
Dip top and bottom in margarine and put in a baking pan.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Place soy sauce in a shallow dish; add chicken, turning to coat.
Remove chicken from soy sauce; discard soy sauce.
Combine sesame seed and next 3 ingredients in a large zip-top heavy-duty plastic bag.
Add chicken; seal bag and shake to coat chicken with sesame seed mixture.

title: chocolate dream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line a 10 x 15-inch jellyroll pan with waxed paper. Whisk together cocoa, sugar and boiling water. Cool to lukewarm. Prepare cake mix per package directions, using 1 1/4 cups water and adding cocoa mixture. Spread batter evenly in the pan. Bake 20 minutes or until top looks dry. Invert onto a large wire rack. Remove the pan and waxed paper. Cool.

In a medium bowl, dissolve coffee in milk. Add topping and pudding mixes. Beat on low speed until moistened. Beat at high speed until soft peaks form. Chill 5 minutes. Cut cake crosswise into thirds. Cover each layer with topping. Stack and chill 2 hours.

title: oriental chicken and rice
directions: Saute chicken and garlic in oil until lightly browned, about 4 minutes.
Stir in peppers and mushrooms.
Cook and stir until crisp-tender, 2 to 3 minutes.
Combine water, cornstarch and soy sauce in small bowl, stirring until smooth.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Add ginger and bouillon cube.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Cook one minute.
Spoon over rice and sprinkle with nuts.
Serves 4.

title: brown betty
directions: Mix butter with bread crumbs.
Alternate layers of apples, bread crumbs, sugar and cinnamon (mix together with lemon rind). End with bread crumbs in a buttered baking dish.
Pour water and lemon juice over all.
Cover and bake for 3/4 hour in 375° oven, 1/4 hour longer, uncovered.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Chop shrimp coarsely; set aside.
In bowl, combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Add shrimp.
Serve with crackers. Yield:
16 servings.

title: easy ambrosia
directions: Mix all together.
Let sit for 24 hours (in refrigerator) for best results.
May add raisins, nuts, etc.

title: cornflake chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken parts and pat dry.
Put chicken in a bowl.
Add salad dressing and mix.
Marinate one hour.

title: butterscotch chocolate cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions, using a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cool on a wire rack for 30 minutes.
Using the end of a wooden spoon handle, poke 12 holes in warm cake.
Pour butterscotch topping over cake; cool completely. Spread with whipped topping; sprinkle with crushed candy bars. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender for 30 seconds.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix everything together.
Then add eggs, one at a time.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: perfect peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in 10 x 6-inch pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add egg; toss until crumbly. Sprinkle over peaches.
Drizzle with oleo.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: puttanesca sauce
directions: Saute garlic in the oil until soft and golden brown.
Add the tomatoes; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add olives, capers, basil and red pepper.
Simmer in uncovered pot for 20 minutes, stirring it gently, until sauce has thickened.
Great on any type of pasta.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add zucchini, applesauce and orange juice.
Stir well.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix sour cream, mayo and dry dressing mix together; set aside. Bake cornbread. When cool, crumble portion into bottom of 3 qt. (or larger) clear bowl. Layer beans, corn, cheese, onions, pepper, tomatoes, bacon and dressing mix (thin layer-about a cup). Repeat layers. Top with remaining dressing mix. Add a little cheese on top.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and pour in boiling water (enough to mix well).
Let cool enough to pat into patties.
Fry in about 1-inch of hot oil until evenly browned.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix everything except spice bag and vinegar and cook 30 minutes. Then add spice bag and vinegar and cook until thick.

title: great american sloppy joes
directions: In a skillet, brown hamburger, salt and onion together.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken with rice
directions: Spray large skillet with non-stick spray, and brown chicken. Stir in barbecue sauce water, corn and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes. Stir in rice, cover. Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes, until rice is ready. A 12 oz can white chicken can be substituted for the cubed chicken.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs (don't overbeat).
Blend in spices, stir in hot milk.
Fold in bread, cheese and meat.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. You may use bacon or ham or just one.

title: instant fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set until firm.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Divide nuts and morsels in the bottoms of two unbaked pie shells.
Over this, pour mixture of butter, eggs, sugar and corn syrup.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
(If the chocolate morsels are left out, the result will be a basic pecan pie.)

title: flan
directions: Cook sugar and water on high, stirring until caramelized.
Mix eggs and yolks, vanilla, cream, half and half and canned milk. Heat.
Stir a little with a whisk.
Pour the caramel in bottom of a deep dish pie plate.
Pour egg mixture over.
Cook at 325° in water bath.

title: pizza dough homemade
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, yeast and salt.
Add water and oil; mix in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until dough is smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Cover; let rest on floured surface 10 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Freeze 1/2 for future use.

title: plain and easy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If needed, add small amount of water over mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: fettucine san clemente(6 servings)
directions: Cook noodles according to package instructions.
Meanwhile, saute vegetables and garlic in butter until they are crisp-tender. Add remaining ingredients; cook until hot, but do not boil.
Pour over hot pasta, tossing to coat noodles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: apple crisp(heart healthy and low-fat)
directions: Place sliced apples in a deep baking dish; sprinkle with lemon juice, lemon zest, sugar and cinnamon.
Combine remaining ingredients in another bowl; pour over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together meal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Stir in milk.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add melted shortening. Pour into well-greased baking pan or muffin tins.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: peanut butter-chocolate kiss cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter; gradually add 1/2 cup sugar and brown sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and then roll in 1/4 cup sugar; place 2 inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven; press a chocolate Kiss into the center of each cookie.
Return to oven for an additional 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: orange and pear jello
directions: Mix orange Jell-O according to directions using pear juice instead of cold water.
Mix Dream Whip, fold in Jell-O and add pears.

title: rosa marina salad
directions: Add the juice from pineapple and oranges to sugar, eggs, flour and salt.
Cook until thick.
When macaroni is chilled thoroughly, fold in fruit and Cool Whip.
Chill again.
Makes a large bowl full.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and sugar in bowl.
In another bowl, mix drained pineapple, partially thawed strawberries and juice, bananas and Cool Whip.
Add to creamed mixture.
Put into a loaf pan or 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze solid.
Can be taken from freezer and sliced to serve on lettuce.
Champagne Salad can be used as salad or served with a wafer for dessert.

title: off beat carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain and put in 1-quart casserole. Combine mayonnaise, horseradish, onions, salt and pepper.
Stir into carrots.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: southern delight macaroons
directions: Mix corn flakes, coconut and pecans in large mixing bowl.
Mix sugar, syrup, evaporated milk, butter and salt in a medium size saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Stirring constantly, continue cooking over medium heat to 234° (soft ball in cold water) or about 10 minutes after mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Gradually pour over corn flake mixture, stirring to coat well.
Stir gently so as not to break corn flakes any more than necessary.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet, shaping into mounds lightly with fingers and allow to set.
Yields 38 to 40 macaroons.

title: meringue for pie(won't weep)
directions: Cook until thick and clear 2 tablespoons of sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cool completely.
In mixing bowl, beat egg whites, salt, vanilla and 1/3 cup of sugar until stiff.
Add cooked ingredients and beat until smooth.
Spread on top of pie and brown in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: diet cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until dry; let cool.
Add applesauce, sweetener, eggs and oil.
Blend in 2 cups of flour, vanilla, spices and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes in a tube pan or 30 minutes in a large loaf pan.

title: microwave sugar glazed walnuts
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, place butter.
Microwave on High for 1 minute or until melted. Stir in brown sugar and cinnamon. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Mix well to combine butter and sugar. Add nuts and mix to coat.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes. Spread out onto waxed paper and cool slightly.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 1 pound.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix everything together.
Shape into a microwave baking dish. Make an indentation in the top of the meat loaf.
Cook, uncovered, on Medium for 25 to 30 minutes until the center is cooked.
Cover and let it stand for 10 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix together and put in ice cream machine.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: south of the border dip
directions: Mix beans and sausage mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch dish. Cover with layer of sour cream.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and cheese melts.
Dip with corn chips.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add onion and cook until tender. Add onion, tomatoes and seasonings.
Arrange layers of tomatoes and mixture and crumbs in greased baking dish, ending with crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake in 375° oven 30 to 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients together.
Pour into 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with fried onions.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carol remke's rum cake
directions: Blend cake mix with eggs, pudding and the remaining three ingredients.
Beat for two minutes and pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
While cake is cooking, prepare icing.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar, then add the sifted flour.
Mix well.
Add the crushed potato chips and vanilla.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoonful on a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: green chili
directions: Brown pork.
Add pork, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Drain juice of tomatoes into stock pot.
Chop tomatoes; add to pot.
Add green chilies and jalapeno pepper and 2 cups water.
Stir well and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Whisk together flour and 1/3 cup water until smooth.
Add to chili mixture; stir constantly until well blended and slightly thickened.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve with warmed tortillas.

title: italian style cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans; mix well.
Shape into balls and roll in pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and rest of ingredients.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° until they start to crack, approximately 15 minutes.
Remove from oven, top with a Kiss and leave on cookie sheet
5 minutes.
Remove.

title: hot spice punch
directions: Place spices in percolator basket.
Perk liquid and sugar in a large coffeepot.

title: whale soup
directions: Cut up whale, onions, potatoes, carrots into bite size pieces. This takes 3 to 4 days.
Add water.
Cook well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Invite the whole village to dinner.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except corn flakes and 3/4 stick of melted butter in large bowl.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine corn flakes and butter.
Spread on top of potato mixture. Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Chop onion and saute in oil or butter until clear.
Mix all ingredients in a large pan.
Mix well.
Heat and eat.
Enjoy.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until thick. Add coconut and vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue. Sprinkle with coconut and place in slow oven to brown.

title: best little cookie in texas(circa 1954)
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Stir in cinnamon and cloves.
Combine pecans, dates, raisins and flour; add to sugar mixture.
Beat well.
Gradually beat in butter.
Mix soda in water and add to dough.
Mix thoroughly.
This dough must be stiff.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 275° for 20 minutes.
Yields 20 dozen small cookies.

title: krispy cheese balls
directions: Mix well the flour, butter, cayenne pepper, salt and cheese. Add Rice Krispies; mix gently but well.
Roll in 1/2-inch balls. Place on baking sheet and flatten slightly with a glass or palm of your hand.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook veggies in butter until soft.
Add broth and bayleaf. Cook several minutes on medium high heat to meld all flavors. Puree in blender or food processor till smooth.
Put back in pan and add 1/2 c. cream.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Serve with a dollop of sour cream in center.

title: zesty black bean - potato salad
directions: Boil Idaho potatoes in their jackets 30 minutes or until tender.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine onion, sour cream, mayonnaise, celery salt, cumin, pepper, garlic, vinegar and tomatoes and green chilies.
Fold in black beans.
Coarsely chop the potatoes (will measure about 8 cups) and gradually add to the sauce, gently coating the potatoes.
Chill several hours before serving on a platter covered with lettuce or spinach leaves. Garnish with tomato wedges and sprinkle with snipped cilantro. Serves 10 to 12 generously.

title: amber's favorite salsa
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a food processor and process (but not too much).
Better next day.

title: mayonnaise cake or salad dressing cake
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Bake in 3 x 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured for 25 to 38 minutes at 350°.
Shorter time for 2 layer pans.

title: peach cobbler(low-fat version)
directions: Spray a glass 12 x 9 x 2-inch dish with Pam.
Cover bottom of dish with drained peaches.
Sprinkle dry Butter Buds over peaches. Combine Bisquick, sugar and milk; pour mixture over peaches.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
It is done when the top is slightly browned and firm.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in order given in a serving dish or large salad bowl.
Put mayonnaise on top and seal.
Let stand for 2 hours or more before serving.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake for one hour in 350° oven.
Great served warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
Doesn't require frosting.

title: hot dish sausage bake
directions: Combine sausage and hamburger.
Brown and drain. Cook egg noodles according to package directions.
Combine all in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: amish cookies
directions: Whip
the sugar, powdered sugar, oil and butter together.
Add eggs and whip
until light and fluffy.
Add flour and other ingredients until mixed.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: scampi
directions: Mince garlic and blend with salt, basil and oregano.
Heat oleo, olive oil and garlic mixture in skillet.
When very hot, add shrimp and cook until firm and pink, about 3 minutes.
Serve over your favorite pasta.
Sprinkle with cheese and black pepper.

title: sausage cake
directions: Mix sugar with sausage.
Add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together and add sausage mixture alternately with coffee.
Add vanilla
and
beat well.
Add fruit and nuts.
Pour into well-greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Roll graham cracker to crumbs; mix well with sugar and melted butter.
Press into pan, then put in your filling.
Save a few crumbs for top.
Bake in 375° oven for ten minutes.
Top with whipped cream.
Any stewed fruits may be used for filling.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Put peppers and water in blender and pulverize.
Next put all ingredients in large pot except Certo and food coloring.
Soft boil for 5 minutes.
Skim top.
Add Certo and green food coloring.
Pour into boiled jars and seal.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil
in bowl.
Add pumpkin and mix. Sift dry ingredients together
twice.
Mix
with
pumpkin mixture. Bake in greased and
floured
tube
pan
minutes at 350°, then reduce oven to 275° for 30 minutes.

title: lo-cal fruit trifle
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Break up angel food cake.
Put layer of cake, layer of pudding, layer of fruit; repeat.
Last layer, top with Cool Whip and garnish with fresh fruit.

title: fried wild rabbits
directions: Refrigerate rabbit overnight in milk and salt solution.
Pat dry.
Sprinkle pieces with pepper and paprika.
Roll in flour. Fry in oil until brown, approximately 20 minutes.
Pour off drippings.
Add wine and butter to skillet.
Cover tightly and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.
Preparation Time:
45 minutes.

title: cookie dunk pudding
directions: *Or use Jell-O cook and serve pudding and pie filling prepared with milk as directed on package.
Refrigerate 2 hours before assembling dessert.

title: lemon icebox cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water. Beat egg yolks lightly. Add sugar, lemon juice and rind. Cook in double boiler until thick, about 15 minutes. Remove from stove and add gelatin. Beat the egg whites very stiff. Add to cooked mixture. Beat all together. Line spring-form pan with ladyfingers and also the sides. Pour in mixture. Set overnight in refrigerator. Top with whipped cream. Can also make it with chocolate pudding instead of lemon.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat oil, eggs and sugar.
Add pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients and add to cream cheese mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Put into greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until it tastes done.
Cool and ice with a cream cheese icing.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar and 2 cups water.
Heat to melting and add other juices.
Makes 1 gallon.
Can freeze Kool-Aid in ice cube trays.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in prunes and milk.
Sift in dry ingredients and beat until fluffy. Bake in a greased, floured tube pan or square pan (350°) for 30 minutes or until straw comes out clean.

title: garlic grits
directions: Cook grits until tender.
Add cheese and margarine.
Add egg mixture and milk.
Add garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce. Bake in greased dish, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Line bottom of pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk; when getting firm, fold in Cool Whip.
Pour on top of graham crackers and put another layer of crackers on top.
Frost with chocolate frosting and refrigerate for 24 to 48 hours.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine jello and water, stirring until jello is dissolved. Then fold in all at once the strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and pecans. Turn half of strawberry mixture into 12 x 8 x 2 dish as the first layer. Refrigerate until firm.

title: chicken rollatini
directions: Pound each chicken breast to 1/4-inch thickness.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Put a slice of ham on the top of each breast along with cheese and sage.
Roll up each breast and secure with wooden toothpicks.
Roll in flour, dusting off excess.
Heat oil and butter in 10-inch skillet over moderate heat.
Add chicken and fry 5 minutes, turning once, until brown.
Cover pan and simmer 10 to 15 minutes over low heat until chicken is tender.
Transfer to platter and cover to keep warm.
Remove any cheese from skillet. Add broth and wine to skillet and boil 3 minutes over high heat, stirring constantly, until syrupy.
Stir in cream and boil 1 minute.
Pour over chicken.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: five-can casserole
directions: Combine all the canned ingredients. Place in a casserole dish and top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: crock pot stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain. Place everything in crock pot. Cook at least 4 hours on high.

title: edna's favorite oatmeal cake
