directions: Mix hot water and oats; set aside. Mix and beat sugars and cooking oil. Beat in eggs. Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt. Add to mixture. Add oats to mixture.
Cook in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix above ingredients in order given except nuts and marshmallows.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with nuts and marshmallows.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then lower temperature to 350° and bake until set.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Saute ham and green onion in 3 tablespoons melted butter in a large skillet until onions are tender.
Add eggs and cook over medium-high heat, stirring to form large, soft curds.
When eggs are set, stir in mushrooms and cheese sauce.
Spoon eggs into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar, a little at a time; then eggs, one at a time.
Continue to beat.
Add flour in three parts.
Add milk and rest of flour alternately, then add sour cream and coconut and flavorings.
Put in a floured pan.
Put in a cold oven and turn heat to 325°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: golden melon frozen yogurt
directions: Combine melon, orange peel and sugar in food processor. Process until pureed.
Let stand 1 minute, add gelatin and juice. Cook and stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Add to fruit mixture.
Stir in yogurt.
Freeze in an ice cream maker according to the manufacturer's directions.
Allow to ripen for 4 hours. Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings; 0 total fat.

title: crock-pot stew beef
directions: Put beef, onion and soups in crock-pot.
Cook on low setting 9 to 10 hours.

title: chicken dip
directions: Season chicken breasts and place on baking sheet and bake about 25 minutes in oven at about 250 degrees.
Remove from oven and cool.
When cool, shred.
Take shredded chicken and place in medium bowl.
Mix in cream cheese, mayonnaise, Cheddar cheese, green chile peppers and jalapeno pepper.
Mix well.
Spoon chicken mixture into a baking dish.
Bake uncovered for about 30 minutes or until edges are golden brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight. Serve.

title: rice, broccoli and shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice, broccoli and shrimp separately.
Set aside.
Mix cheese and soups.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add broccoli. Layer rice in bottom of a 5 x 9 baking dish.
Add a layer of soup mixture and a layer of shrimp.
Repeat layers.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and spread in a 12-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: legend's chicken salad
directions: Cook the chicken breasts with chicken bouillon, salt, pepper, bay leaf, celery seeds and bouquet garni. (I just boil with "poultry seasoning" already mixed; it's easier.) After cooling, cut meat into bite size pieces.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in punch bowl.
Add vanilla ice cream and serve.

title: deluxe pecan chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
In a bowl, combine butter and brown sugar. Beat until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla extract.
Beat until light and fluffy. Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in morsels and pecans. Drop by well rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Allow to stand 2 to 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheet. Cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sugared citrus strips
directions: Remove peel from fruit in long continuous strips; cut into 1/4 x 1 1/2-inch pieces.
In medium saucepan, cover peel with cold water.
Bring to a boil and cook until tender, pouring off water and adding fresh cold water several times; drain.
With spoon, remove white inner portion of peel.

title: mango ginger relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight. Great relish for fish, chicken or pork.

title: cherry or fruit cobbler
directions: Pour batter on top of butter.
Spoon cherries on butter. Bake at 350° until brown.
Add any kind of fruit.

title: six-week muffins
directions: Combine bran, sugar and flour, sifted with soda and salt in a very large bowl or dishpan.
Add mixture of eggs, buttermilk and oil; mix well.
May be refrigerated in covered bowl for weeks. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ole fashioned cobbler
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Mix dry ingredients together. Alternately mix sugar mixture, dry ingredients and milk to form a smooth batter.
Pour batter into 2-quart casserole.
Spread 2 cups cherries over batter.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar on the fruit, then pour 1/2 cup juice (or whatever has accumulated from the fruit) over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Put roast in roaster.
Cover with beer and chili sauce.
Cook for 1 hour at 350 degrees covered.
Add vegetables and cook for 3 more hours covered.

title: chili peppers
directions: Saute bacon.
Add onion and garlic, saute 3 to 4 minutes. Add peppers and tomatoes. Cover and saute 5 minutes.
Add salt. Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes on low.

title: italian style meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Mix all ingredients by hand in a large bowl.
Roll into approximately 80 - 90 1- inch meatballs.
Place on two ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 450°
for 8 to 10 minutes or until meatballs are browned.

title: jiffy rolls
directions: When mixture of water, salt and oleo boils, reduce heat.
Using a wooden spoon, vigorously stir in the flour.

title: chili, vegetarian-style
directions: Heat oil in medium Dutch oven and saute garlic for 1 minute until it begins to color.
Add onion and cook for 3 minutes until softened.
Add seasonings and green pepper and cook for 1 minute longer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes until thickened.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Combine dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add eggs one at a time.
Alternate adding milk and dry ingredients.
Add flavorings last.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Place in a COLD oven.
Turn to 300° and bake 2 hours.

title: creamy chicken bake
directions: Place chicken breasts in shallow pan.
Place a slice of Swiss cheese on each breast.
Mix soup and wine; stir.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over.
Drizzle with melted butter. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: cajun chicken drumsticks
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
In a bowl mix together all the spices and salt with the garlic, tomato puree, lemon juice and oil.
Wipe the chicken and, using a pastry brush, cover them with the spice paste.
Place the drumsticks in a roasting pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until the skin turns a deep brown and is quite crisp.
Serve the drumsticks with rice and fresh salad.

title: ground beef and rice casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions. Add soup, water and rice.
Mix well. Pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pumpkin drops
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, pumpkin, orange peel and shortening.
Stir in flour, powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake until light brown (8 to 10 minutes).
Cool and frost.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: salsa dip
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Amounts are up to you.
Layer according to ingredient listing in a 9 x 9 pan or larger depending on the number of people.

title: ham and bacon stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook on high setting until stew begins to boil.
Turn to low and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over toast points, biscuits or noodles. Serves 8.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Let ice cream melt until it is soft enough that you are able to stir it.
While the ice cream is melting, "mash" Oreo cookies up in the food processor or hand-held food chopper.
When the ice cream is melted, stir the Oreos into the ice cream, saving a little for the topping.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch glass container. Place into freezer.
When hard, put Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with leftover Oreos.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well; shape into a narrow loaf. Let set for at least 8 hours or overnight.
Slice.
Fry pieces in shortening until brown.
Put slices in a roaster.
Mix the soup with 1 can milk; pour over all pieces.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: mushroom pepper pork chops
directions: Brown well the pork chops in skillet. Add rest of ingredients. Simmer for 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in a long pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and top with icing.

title: papaya guacamole
directions: Place all ingredients in a food processor fitted with a steel blade, process for 5 to 10 seconds.
Scrape sides and process for another 10 seconds or until it forms a chunky puree.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice; blend well.
Add eggs, oil, milk, vanilla and cooked prunes.
Add nuts and mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased 8-inch round pan (makes 2 layers) or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Bake at 350°.
Top with Buttermilk Icing.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Add lemon juice to milk.
Add pineapple and nuts and fold in Cool Whip.
Put into pie shells.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
(Fresh blueberries or strawberries may be used instead of pineapple.)

title: baking mix(mock "bisquick")
directions: Combine dry ingredients and work Crisco in until it resembles corn meal.
Store in an airtight container in a cool area.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Dip pork chops in batter and coat with bread crumbs.
Place in a slightly oiled skillet.
Cook for half an hour until golden brown on the outside. Bake in oven at 400° for another 15 minutes, until meat is thoroughly cooked.
Check on often because of thickness.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Combine applesauce, cocoa and soda.
Beat the soda and cocoa into the applesauce, then add sugar and butter or oleo.
Dredge the raisins, nuts and candied fruit with part of flour.
Add to the batter mixture.
Add vanilla, salt and flour.
Beat by hand.
Line an angel food cake pan with wax paper.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: soft 100% whole wheat bread
directions: Work down every 20 minutes for 3 hours.
Shape.
Put in greased pans.
Prick with fork and let rise in warm place, about 1 hour.

title: hawaiian delight cake
directions: Bake cake mix by package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 3/4 cup crumb mixture for top.
Combine pudding and milk; beat 2 minutes.
Add ice cream.
Blend until smooth.
Spread over crust. Top with Cool Whip and crumbs.
Refrigerate, but do not freeze.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix jello, boiling water and cream cheese; let congeal (in freezer, 30 minutes).
Add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Stir well and refrigerate.

title: pop's pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta 1 minute; add onion (sliced lengthwise).
One minute later, add carrot (sliced in small sticks).
One minute later, add celery (sliced in small sticks).
When pasta is al dente stage (5 minutes), drain.
Add vinegar, sugar, ripe olives (cut up) and optionals.
Stir in salad dressing; add cut up ripe peppers.
Cool as quickly as possible.
Voila.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
On greased baking sheets, arrange the pecan halves in groups of 3, flat side down, in Y shapes.
Place a caramel on top of each cluster.
Place in oven until the caramels soften, about 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and flatten the caramels over the pecans with a buttered spoon.
Cool slightly. Melt the chocolate using a double boiler over simmering water. Dip the turtles into the chocolate and cool on wax paper.
Store in tightly covered containers in a cool place.

title: impossible chicken 'n broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle broccoli, 1 cup of the cheese, the chicken and onion in pie plate.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Line a 9X5-inch loaf pan with foil. Spray foil with cooking spray. Combine milk and egg in a large bowl; add bread crumbs, basil, parsley and pepper. Stir until blended. Add onion and bell pepper, mix well. Add beef and mix to combine ingredients. Pour into prepared loaf pan. Do not pack. Spread topping over meat loaf. Bake until cooked through, about 1 hour. Remove from oven to wire rack. Let stand for 5 minutes. Lift meat loaf out of pan and place on serving platter, remove foil. Can prepare ahead as recipe directs, cover and keep refrigerated for 2 days. Serve cold or reheat in warm oven.

title: bananas foster
directions: Cut bananas in half crosswise and lengthwise.
Brush with lemon juice.
Melt brown sugar and butter in skillet.
Add bananas and cook until tender (about 3 - 4 minutes), turning once. Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Drizzle banana liqueur over all. Heat rum in small saucepan over low heat, just until warm.
Remove from heat.
Ignite.
Pour liqueur over bananas.
Serve with vanilla ice cream!

title: teriyaki fried chicken
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Mix honey, soy sauce and garlic.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: deer or beef jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Cut meat into long thin strips.
Place meat in large air-tight container and pour mixture over meat.
Let marinate in refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours.
Stir meat every 8 hours.
Cover oven rack with aluminum foil and place strips of meat on foil.
Bake between 120° to 150° for 6 hours, turning meat over at 3 hours.
Keep oven door cracked open at all times.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, sour cream, almonds, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Put this into a buttered casserole dish.
Mix together Ritz crackers and margarine.
Spread this on top of the mixture in the casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: easy veg-all casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven until casserole bubbles.
Place croutons on top and brown.

title: punch
directions: Bring to boil water and sugar.
Pour into large bowl.
Add vodka, orange juice and lemonade.
Stir and freeze for at least 24 hours.
Serve slush with 7-Up.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in an electric skillet and set thermostat at 280°.
Bring to a boil, cook 5 minutes longer stirring constantly.
Turn off skillet and add the marshmallows and peanut butter; stir until well blended.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool, cut into squares.

title: easy pudding milkshake
directions: Pour milk into shaker.
(If you don't have a shaker, you can use any large size container with a lid.)
Add the pudding mix and the ice cream.
Put lid on shaker.
Make sure the lid is on tight and that it doesn't leak.
Shake very hard for at least 1 minute. (Be sure to hold both the top and bottom of the shaker or container when shaking.)
Open shaker.
Pour into glass.
Serve right away. Makes 1 serving.

title: spring salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Best if refrigerated overnight before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into ball.	Roll in nuts.

title: punch
directions: Mix well and add lots of ice.
If too strong, add more water or ice.
Frozen strawberries or maraschino cherries may be added at serving time.

title: honey bon cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, water, eggs and sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts. Pour 1/2 of the sugar mixture, then pour the rest of batter and sprinkle the rest of sugar mixture over the top of cake.
Take a knife and swirl in the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and blend all ingredients together.
Chill and shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans and sprinkle with paprika.

title: crisp sweet pickles
directions: Boil and pour it over the cukes. Drain the next day; heat syrup to boiling and pour over cukes. Repeat for 4 days (5 days in all). Drain. Put pickles in jars. Heat syrup to boiling. Pour over the cukes and seal the jars. ENJOY!

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water for 25 minutes, or until tender.
Stir frequently.
Drain.
Separately, cook ground beef. Arrange noodles, meat, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for approximately 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Early a.m. place ribs in slow cooker and pour almost a bottle of barbecue sauce over ribs.
(Ribs may be frozen or thawed.)
Set cooker on low and allow to cook all day.

title: bonnie pieri's grilled pork chops(smittie's daughter)
directions: Combine oil and next 6 ingredients.
Arrange pork chops in a single layer, flat in a large sealable plastic bag.
Pour marinade over chops. Seal bag and freeze. When ready to use, thaw chops in refrigerator overnight.
Cook over hot coals on grill 20 to 30 minutes until juices run clear.
May also be browned in frying pan with 2 to 3 tablespoons oil, then cooked 20 minutes longer. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Layer half each of sweet potatoes and apples in an 8-inch baking dish coated with spray or butter.

title: italian sausage appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 150 balls.
Can be frozen and reheated at serving time.

title: crunchy nut lentil roast
directions: Saute onions and celery in small amount of water.
Blend lentils and soy sauce in blender.
Add more water as needed.
Add other ingredients.
If too thin, add bread crumbs.
Put in Pam-sprayed baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Serve with tomato sauce.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Bring 1 cup water and raisins to a boil.
Mix 1/2 cup water, egg yolks, flour and sugar.
Cook until thick.
Add raisins, vanilla and vinegar.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: quick apple dessert
directions: Beat together the first 7 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Spread in 10-inch deep pie dish.
Combine apple pie filling, lemon juice, cinnamon and allspice; spoon over batter.
Do not press into batter.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy ham casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower in salted water for 10 to 12 minutes. Combine ham and mushrooms.
Melt butter; stir in flour.
Add milk; cook until thickened.
Add cheese and sour cream; stir until cheese melts.
Combine with ham and cauliflower mixture.
Stir together bread crumbs and remaining butter; sprinkle over top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Brown chops in a small amount of fat. Then arrange in a large baking dish. Combine the chopped celery, green pepper, onions and tomato sauce in a saucepan and heat to boiling. Pour over the chops and then bake in a covered dish until tender at 350°, which is about an hour.

title: "souper" oven pot roast
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix together 2 soups.
Place beef on heavy foil and pour soup over and around meat.
Bring long sides of foil together and fold over in a secure fold.
Pull up short ends of foil; fold securely to keep in steam.
Place on baking sheet or shallow pan.
Roast approximately 4 hours.
Test for doneness during last 1/2 hour.
Meat is extremely tender.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Blend in flour, add bouillon and mix well.
Cook until thick.
Stir in mushrooms, Worcestershire and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot.

title: chicken curry
directions: In a large pot, heat butter; add the onion, garlic, celery, bay leaf, parsley, mustard, apple and ham.
Cook eight minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: steamed spiced shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp, drain in colander and put in pot with shells on (no water added).
Put butter and all seasoning on top of shrimp. Steam for 20 minutes with lid on.
Stir often.
Fire hot for 10 minutes, then low for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place water and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Use extra 1/4 cup water and cornstarch to make a paste.
Pour paste into boiling water.
Cook until clear (2 to 3 minutes).
Remove from stove and add jello.
Pour over berries which have been prepared and sliced into crust.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Spread in 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Bring water to a boil in saucepan. Add grits; reduce heat. Cook, covered, using package directions. Stir in margarine, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage layer. Beat eggs with milk in bowl. Stir in cheese. Pour over layers. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set. May chill or freeze until needed.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a cookie
sheet
with foil. Fold the Worcestershire into the egg whites.
Fold
in pecans. Spread the pecans on the cookie sheet.
Combine
garlic
salt, salt
and cayenne and place in a shaker.
Sprinkle evenly over the pecans. Bake for 20 minutes, or until crunchy.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Place bread crumbs in a bowl.
In a pot heat milk and butter. Pour over bread crumbs.
Add remaining ingredients except eggs and tuna.
Mix well.
Gradually stir in eggs.
Place tuna in casserole.
Cover with egg mixture.
Place casserole in pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: o.j. punch
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and chill.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Add margarine (soft) and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Similar to custard pie.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Spread breasts flat; fold cheese and ham slices to fit on top. Fold breasts over filling; secure with toothpicks.
On waxed paper, mix flour and paprika.
Coat chicken pieces.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, melt margarine and cook chicken until browned on both sides.
Add wine and bouillon.
Reduce heat, cover and
simmer 30 minutes until tender.
Remove toothpicks.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in small saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Mix with spoon until thick enough to spread. Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain most of grease.
Add other ingredients and let simmer until potatoes are done.

title: vegetables with dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with cucumbers, carrots, celery, cauliflower, turnip sticks, broccoli, etc.

title: marinated veggie salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, bell pepper and green onions.
Add French-style green beans, corn, sliced green beans and carrots.
Add combination of celery, broccoli and cauliflower.
Put in a large covered dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold. Serves 10 to 12.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Put oatmeal in small amounts in a blender until it turns to powder. Mix together flour and oatmeal.
Add salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix together all ingredients.
Add chocolate chips and plain Hershey bar and any kind of nuts.
Make a ball about the size of a golf ball.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for about 6 minutes or until cookie has flattened.
This recipe can be halved.

title: easy to do quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle pie shell with both cheeses. Add vegetables to pie shell.
Beat eggs, milk, onion and oregano together in large bowl; pour over cheese and vegetables.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large pan, put 2 cups water, chicken broth and onion; let it heat and simmer, then add your cream of chicken, your cream of celery, hash browns and creamer.
Let simmer and boil about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots (sliced diagonally) until barely done.
Slice onion and separate into rings.
Slice green pepper in slivers. Make sauce with remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables. Marinate overnight.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: baked dove breasts
directions: Dip dove in flour; fry until golden brown.
Place in casserole and cover with the soup and seasonings which have been mixed together.
Bake until done.

title: albondigas(meatball soup)
directions: Put water in pot to boil.
Add salt.
Mix all other ingredients.
Make meatballs size desired.
Put them in boiling water.
Simmer like soup for 1 1/2 hours.
Vegetables may be added, if desired, in the last 1/2 hour.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Cut chicken in bite size pieces.
In large saucepan or Dutch oven in 2 tablespoons vegetable oil, saute chicken and onions until done.
Add 4 cups water, tomatoes, carrots and pasta.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook until pasta is almost tender (about 10 minutes).
Add zucchini and parsley. Cover and cook 5 minutes more.
Serves 5.

title: low-fat tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles, onion, celery and carrots according to directions for the noodles omitting oil and salt.
Drain well.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Saut celery and onion in butter until transparent. Add vegetable mixture to combined bread crumbs and seasonings. Mix lightly.

title: chocolate pie(low calorie)
directions: Mix pudding and milk together and pour into crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Note:
You may use only pecans and English walnuts, if desired (4 cups of each).

title: creamed ham casserole
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet over low heat.
Add onions, green pepper and mushrooms.
Cook until soft.
Stir in ham, lemon juice and sour cream.
Heat 3 minutes.
Arrange half of the noodles in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour in ham mixture.
Top with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 4.

title: salmon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill. Serve cold.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs, sugar, butter, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake until firm (about 50 minutes).
Cool on a rack.
Serve garnished with chopped nuts or whipped cream, if desired.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Thoroughly cream together the shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in the peanut butter.
Sift the flour, soda and salt; stir into the creamed mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each cookie with back of floured fork to make crisscross.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for about 9 minutes, or until light brown.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: beans, beans and more beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon.
Drain grease off.
Stir in all cans of beans.
Add remaining ingredients and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix together the cream cheese and condensed milk.
Blend in whipped topping.
Fold together fruit and whipped topping mixture. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover; freeze until firm.
Cut into squares to serve, or freeze in individual dishes.

title: creamy cauliflower salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables; toss lightly to coat.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers, in bowl and form into a ball.
Refrigerate 10 to 12 hours.
Take out of refrigerator 1/2 hour before serving.
Serve on crackers.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon.
Pour off drippings, returning 3 tablespoons to pan.
Add onion, sliced in rings; cook until slightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients and crumble bacon.
Add dash of pepper and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer a minute.
Top with crumbled bacon.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine rhubarb, sugar and salt.
Add flour and mix gently. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Slightly beat egg yolk and add enough milk to make 1/4 cup.
Drizzle over pie.
Top with crust.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes or until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust.

title: chicken filet picasso
directions: Fry chicken breast in butter or margarine until golden brown. Add pepper, broccoli, corn, soup and water.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve with small boiled potatoes or with rice.

title: oven meatballs
directions: Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Remove cover and continue to bake another 1/2 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter.
In bowl beat eggs.
Add milk, corn, salt and pepper.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Heat 1-inch of oil in a skillet to 375°.
Beat eggs well in large mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Stir into batter until smooth.
Cover opening of funnel with finger.
Pour 1/4 cup batter into a wide mouth funnel.
When ready to fry, release finger and run batter into hot oil, using a slow, wide circular motion and maintaining as steady a stream as possible.
Fry, turning once, until golden brown.
Fry for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towel.
Repeat until all batter is used.
Sprinkle generously with confectioners sugar.
Best served warm.
Makes 10 large funnel cakes.
You may use Pioneer Beignet French Doughnut mix.

title: lemon-lime yogurt pie
directions: Combine the graham cracker crumbs, apple juice concentrate and cinnamon.
Mix well with a fork to blend.
Sprinkle on the bottom of pie plate coated with butter-flavored nonstick spray.
Pat into place.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: upside-down cake(bake auction)
directions: Line two 8 or 9-inch pans or one 9 x 13-inch pan with foil and grease.
Melt shortening in pan.
Divide brown sugar between 2 pans.
Add cherries and pineapple.
Beat together egg yolks, boiling water and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar and baking powder into egg yolk mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or longer.
Test with cake tester.
Turn out immediately.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into two greased 9 x 10-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° until nice and brown on top, about 40 minutes.
Keeps well for 2 or 3 days.

title: beef in potato casserole(microwave)
directions: Crumble beef in large microwaveable bowl.
Cook on High 4 to 5 minutes or until done.
Stir in broccoli, onions, soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and spices.
Cook, uncovered, on High 6 minutes, stirring halfway through.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken by boiling in water until tender.
Mix together cooked chicken (chopped or bite size), mayonnaise and sweet pickles; chill.
Just before serving, mix in almonds and grapes and top with poppy seed.
Serve on lettuce or with crescent rolls.

title: english toffee candy
directions: Melt
butter in 2-quart
pan.
Gradually
stir
in
the sugar. Add syrup and water.
Cook
to 290° on candy thermometer.
Add 1 cup nuts.
Cook
minutes more.
Pour candy onto greased cookie sheet and
let cool.
Melt chocolates together. Spread with 1/2 of melted
chocolate
mixture and top with 1/2 of remaining nuts. Cool
until
chocolate
is set.
Turn over and cover other side with remaining chocolate and nuts.
Chill briefly and break into pieces.
"My
favorite thing to make at Christmas."

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bone and cut into cubes.
In a pan, melt margarine and add packet of seasoning in stuffing mix.
To this, add both cans of soup (undiluted) and one cup broth.
Let this come to
boil, then remove from heat.
Add chicken and bread crumbs; be sure to mix well.
This should not be too dry, so if you need to, add more broth.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add the onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt to taste.
Spread on slices of ham.
Roll up (secure with toothpick) and chill.
Slice into small pinwheels.
May be served alone or on a cracker.
Easy and pretty.
(Note:
Dried beef may also be used.)

title: plum kuchen(coo-gan)
directions: Mix all ingredients except plums together; press into a 9-inch tart pan.
Pit plums and cut into quarters.
Arrange in pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: holukies
directions: Steam large head of cabbage 1/2 hour.
Use outer leaves to roll in mixture.
Line bottom of baking dish with cabbage leaves and on top.
Bake for 3 hours in oven at 300°.

title: amish friendship cake
directions: Pour batter into 2 well-greased pans.
Sprinkle powdered sugar and cinnamon on top and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ma's baked beans
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours or high 2 to 3 hours.

title: evelyn's orange pudding
directions: Cover sliced oranges with 1/2 cup sugar for 30 minutes.

title: wackie cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Make 3 holes spaced evenly. In first hole add vinegar, second hole add vanilla in third hole add melted butter.
Pour 1 cup cold water over all.
Mix well, pour into greased pan 9 x 13.
Bake at 350 F for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy pecan pie
directions: Cream very thoroughly the cream cheese, sugar and salt.
Add 1 egg; mix very well.
Spread this mixture in bottom of 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle 1 cup pecans on top of this mixture. Beat 3 eggs and syrup while stirring.
Spoon gently on top of nuts and bake.

title: sweet surprise rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Dip marshmallow in butter, then sugar mixture.
Wrap crescent roll around marshmallow, sealing all edges.
Dip entire roll in butter and then sugar mixture.
Place in muffin tin.
Repeat with remaining marshmallows.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: corn bread fritters
directions: In a large bowl mix all the ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into finger sticks and drop into hot cooking oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: sweet 'n sour salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Marinate for at least 2 days in the refrigerator before using.
Keep refrigerated.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Use a pan that is 2 inches deep.
Break the Oreos into pieces on the bottom of the pan.
After preparing the pudding, spread it over the Oreos.
Top that with the Cool Whip and chill until ready to serve.

title: cucumber-tomato salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a jar; cover tightly with lid and shake well.
Pour dressing over cut vegetables that have been arranged on lettuce leaves.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In a buttered 9 x 12-inch pan, layer bread, cheese, bacon and sausage.
Combine other ingredients and pour over casserole. Cover and let stand overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: texas hot cocoa cake
directions: Stir in self-rising flour sifted with sugar.
Add and mix the buttermilk, cinnamon, vanilla and eggs.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine yeast in mixing bowl with cottage cheese and remaining ingredients.
Add flour gradually to form stiff dough.
Stir well after each addition, then place in greased bowl to rise until double (it took mine about 3 to 4 hours in warm place, not in draft).
Punch down and shape in 2 loaves. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; run margarine over top of loaf as you turn off oven.
Turn onto rack or tea towel to cool.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, water and marshmallows together until the marshmallows are melted.
Put in refrigerator until it starts to set.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple, whipped cream and maraschino cherries.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan and set overnight in refrigerator.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Beat 2 eggs in mixing bowl; add sugar, flour, pineapple (including juice), vanilla, margarine and coconut. Pecans can be added if desired. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 500° for 30 minutes.

title: tabboulle
directions: Chop parsley, leaving very little stem. Chop tomatoes (should be red but firm) = 3 cups. Chop scallions after removing the green tip and the bottom white. Add mint. Add lemon juice (preferably freshly squeezed). Add olive oil (preferably extra virgin). Add 1/3 cup cracked wheat (fine). Leave in fridge for the wheat to soften.

title: canned okra
directions: Boil liquids.
Add okra.
Cook until turn color (2 or 3 minutes).
Put in hot jars and cover with liquid.

title: clam dip
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add all other ingredients (saving a little Parmesan cheese to sprinkle on top).
Cook until soft.
Put in baking dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Can use 1/2 cup bread crumbs and 1/2 cup stuffing.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Saute onions in oleo.
Mix all together.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sticky buns
directions: Put nuts in bottom of sprayed Bundt pan.
Layer rolls on top of nuts.
Sprinkle pudding (dry) over rolls.
Mix brown sugar, oleo and cinnamon over low heat, pour on rolls and let rise overnight.

title: coconut pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Mix
together
eggs,
sugar,
flour,
milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour over melted butter.
Don't stir batter once you have
put it in baking pan.
Cook in oven for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool and serve.

title: escalloped carrots and potatoes
directions: Blend flour to a smooth paste with a little of the milk in a saucepan.
Add remaining milk.
Stir until smooth and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce boils and thickens.
Add seasonings and vegetables and heat to boiling again.

title: cinnamon cookie crisps
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Let tortillas stand at room temperature for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut each into 8 wedges.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 3 to 5 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: meat balls(kjottkaker)
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat with electric beater until smooth.
Form into large balls and fry until dark brown.
Remove from pan and make gravy by adding butter and flour to pan drippings.
Stir until brown.
Add water and boil; stir until thick.
Return meat balls to gravy and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: sweet hearts
directions: Cut sponge cake with 3 or 4-inch heart shaped cookie cutters. Brush top and sides of each heart with preserves.
For marzipan, mix almond paste, corn syrup, almond extract and sugar; stir until mixture forms a stiff dough.
Roll out and trim into 6-inch squares.
Place marzipan over tops and sides of cakes.
Pleat corners and trim bottom edges.
Decorate cakes with leftover marzipan as desired.
